subject: Shipment
body_text:
Hello,

I‚Äôm currently out of the country will be back on 9/5. I saw the email and realized that the vitamins will be delivered and sitting in 100+ degrees heat in my mailbox. Sent from my iPhone On Aug 17, 2024, at 11:07‚ÄØAM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote:  
Ôªø 
Hi Paloma, 
Sorry to hear that Perelel did not work out for you! We would be happy to provide a refund for your first pack in order #579121 less the cost of shipping. Could you kindly complete this short survey to process your request? Once completed, we will go ahead with your refund. You should see this come back on your method of payment within 5-7 business days. (https://forms.gle/WNnSkKDHTtyY4XKx8) You do not need to return your unfinished Perelel Pack to us. 
Additionally, we canceled your subscription so you will not be charged for any future orders. 
Since our vitamins include things like iron, zinc & vitamin C (all essential nutrients we wouldn't want to leave out!), they can irritate your stomach lining especially early in the morning. In order to minimize any symptoms of nausea, we recommend taking
 your Perelel Pack on a full stomach or, even better, splitting up your pills and taking with your meals throughout the day, especially as your body adjusts to a new vitamin routine. Additionally, to minimize any lingering smells or aftertaste, you can also
 pop your Perelel Pack in the freezer prior to taking. You can see more tips & tricks here! (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) 
Unfortunately, the smell is a side effect of natural vitamins, which can smell a bit.. natural! We rely on peppermint leaf powder to neutralize these smells, but with any natural ingredient, there can be fluctuations in the potency in each batch. We also
 avoided sugars, harmful additives, and fillers in our formulations which are often used to completely mask tastes or smells. We've done our best to create a product that is both tolerable and clean! Please see some tips and tricks in this article when adjusting
 to natural vitamins‚ÄîYour Complete Guide to . Taking All Natural Supplements (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) 
If you're ever open to giving us another try, we'd love to offer you a 15% discount using the code COMEBACK15
on your next order. 
Let us know if there is anything else we can help you with! 
Best, 
Team Perelel 
On Sat, Aug 17, 2024, at 12:22 PM, Paloma Cavalheiro < paloma.cav@hotmail.com> wrote: (mailto:paloma.cav@hotmail.com)  
Hello, 
I was having an amazing pregnancy until I started taking this prenatal vitamins. The day I started, I started throwing up daily and spending the entire day nauseous in bed. I thought it was just a coincidence until I stopped taking it for 2 days. Only to confirm
 that the vitamins were the problem. How can you sell prenatal vitamins for the first trimester that make women vomit and be nauseous all day? 
I tried taking it at night instead and I woke up vomiting in the middle of the night. 
How can I return this? 
Thanks 
Paloma

subject: Cannot take supplements anymore
body_text:
Hello! I was unaware that I was subscribed when I ordered these initially. Maybe I‚Äôll blame it on the pregnancy brain. I have really struggled to take these vitamins and still have my initial 2nd trimester pack. I have not opened the 3rd trimester pack thinking I would take them in my 3rd trimester assuming I would love these. They are just too strong for my taste and stomach - honestly I gag every time I open a packet. I tried for about 10 days, and they became more and more difficult to take (and I have not had morning sickness my entire pregnancy). I received another shipment while I was away on travel - unaware I was subscribed. I opened the box not knowing they were another shipment and struggled with the smell of even opening the shipping box. üòÜ I promise I really tried and wanted to love these. I have 1 unopened box of the 2nd trimester supplements, 2 unopened boxes of the 3rd trimester supplements, and 1 partially used box of the 2nd trimester supplements. 

Is there anyway I can send the boxes back for a refund? I am on travel again soon and will need an answer before Friday - when I am out of the country for our babymoon <3 

Thank you so much!

Tiyana

On Aug 13, 2024, at 11:44‚ÄØAM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hi Lauren, 

Thank you for reaching out, we hope you are well. 

Sorry to hear that Perelel did not work out for you! We would be happy to provide a refund for your first pack in order #586653 less the cost of shipping. Could you kindly complete this short survey to process your request? Once completed, we will go ahead with your refund. You should see this come back on your method of payment within 5-7 business days. (https://forms.gle/WNnSkKDHTtyY4XKx8) You do not need to return your unfinished Perelel Pack to us. 

Unfortunately, the smell is a side effect of natural vitamins, which can smell a bit... natural! We rely on peppermint leaf powder to neutralize scent, but often without harmful fillers or additives, there's only so much we can do. We are deeply committed to creating products that are clean, tolerable, and bioavailable. That's why we avoid sugars, harmful additives, and fillers that are commonly used to mask the natural tastes and smells of key ingredients. That said, we are constantly enhancing our formulas to reflect the latest health research as well as capsule innovations and we're proud to report our latest batch has improved smell and taste. 

We also wanted to introduce you to our 1st Trimester Prenatal Vitamin Powder ‚Äî created for the days you just aren't up for taking your pack. Trust us, we've been there! This powder contains the essentials from your prenatal pack to cover your baseline needs in an easy, drinkable format to help ease digestion and nausea. It just needs to be mixed with your cool liquid of choice and taken with a full stomach. This can be particularly helpful when your sense of smell is amplified in the 1st Trimester. (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-vitamin-powder) 

Let us know if you're interested in adding it to your subscription and we can help! 

Feel free to let us know if there is anything else we can help with! 

Best, 
Team Perelel

subject: Re: Order #579767 confirmed
body_text:
Dear Perelel, 
 
I hope you are well. 
 
I am reaching out as unfortunately I am so disappointed with the product. I was recommended your brand by a friend who I trusted. I started taking the vitamins at end of April and stopped taking them a few weeks ago. 
 
The prenatal vitamins have caused me extreme irritation on my skin, face and neck and produced serious cystic acne which I have never experienced before. I have always had amazing skin, so this is extremely abnormal for me. My husband has also seen side effects
 from the men's vitamins from Perelel which I ordered for him at the same time, such as cystic acne and scaring. My face has flared up so much and caused me so much anxiety the past 4 months until I realised what had caused it - Perelel. I stopped taking them
 a few weeks ago and luckily my skin has started to slowly calm down. 
 
I am so disappointed in the product, as well as the added expense it cost me over the summer. I would like to request a refund, a total of $220.81, which adds up to all the subscriptions I had ordered from Perelel. Please see my confirmation receipts attached & images of my skin which I have taken over the course of the 4 months taking the vitamins. 
 
I look forward to hearing from you. 
 
Kindest Regards, 
Selina

subject: First order refund
body_text:
Hi there, 

I‚Äôm reaching out because I‚Äôve been unable to take my first month of prenatals due to the smell and aftertaste of the pills. I know that your return policy allows for a complete refund if unsatisfied within the first 30 days of a subscription. Can you please provide this refund? Let me know if you need anything from me to do so. 

Thanks, 
Nicole 
-- Nicole Farchi-Segal 305.240.2175

subject: Refund
body_text:
Hello, 

I would like to cancel all of my subscriptions. The wrong package was sent to me twice. I am already pregnant and I keep on getting conception packages instead of first or second trimester. I tried to change it and instead had two subscriptions. I have two packages of conception that will not be used. I would like to know if it‚Äôs possible to refund these or change them for a prenatal package as I am already on my first trimester.

Hallie Ross

subject: Question about product
body_text:
Hello, 

A couple of things: 

-Can you add my due date as May 12, 2024? 

-I have two boxes of leftover Conception Support Packs that I am hoping to use (without the CoQ10) so that they don't go to waste. But I noticed that the color of Core Prenatal is much darker than in my previous boxes (it is more black than brown). See attached picture. Do you know what causes this? Is it still good to take even with this color change? 

Than you, 
Lucy

Pro-biotic said best on empty stomach but I also took vitamins on empty stomach , is this why I am nauseous? 
 From: Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> Sent: Wednesday, August 14, 2024 9:14:49 PM To: KARLA VILLANUEVA <houstonleasingqueen@gmail.com> Subject: Re: Reminder: tell us your due date! üîî 
 
 
Hi Karla, 
Thanks for sharing your due date! This will ensure your subscription will automatically update alongside your due date so you receive the right pack for your trimester and into postpartum. 
As a heads up, your Perelel subscription follows the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG) defined trimesters: 
-1st Trimester: Week 0 through Week 13 
-2nd Trimester: Week 14 through Week 27 
-3rd Trimester: Week 28 through Week 40+ 
While the timing of when you start your vitamins with us doesn't always exactly align with your trimester, rest assured all of our packs will keep your needs covered during any overlap weeks! 
Want to connect with moms with a similar due date? Join our Geneva group now! (https://app.geneva.com/invite/997e7178-3982-4480-811f-252001048727) 
Feel free to let us know if you have any additional questions or see more FAQs here :) (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 
Best, 
Team Perelel

subject: Not working out
body_text:
Hi, 

I had signed up for a subscription and I am afraid I have to cancel it. The smell of these pills is unbearable. My husband agrees so this does not seem to be just a pregnancy sensitivity thing. I tried putting them in the freezer for an hour beforehand, reading that that could help, and unfortunately it didn't. I gave it a few days but there is no way I can continue taking these. It's not just the smell, it lingers in an aftertaste. Love the ingredients but unfortunately these are just not working out. Please let me know if I'm able to return my pack for a refund, and please cancel my subscription. 

Best, 

Nicole

Hi Candice, 

Thanks for reaching out! We would be happy to facilitate an exchange. We can process a new charge for a new order for the 2nd Trimester Prenatal Pack now so that you don't miss a day of your vitamins :) We'll also send you a return label for the (https://perelelhealth.com/products/2nd-trimester-prenatal-pack) 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack. Once the return has been received, we'll process a refund less $10 for shipping and restocking. (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack) Please let us know if you would like to proceed! 
Since our vitamins include things like iron, zinc & vitamin C (all essential nutrients we wouldn't want to leave out!), they can irritate your stomach lining especially early in the morning. In order to minimize any symptoms of nausea, we recommend taking your Perelel Pack on a full stomach or, even better, splitting up your pills and taking with your meals throughout the day, especially as your body adjusts to a new vitamin routine. Additionally, to minimize any lingering smells or aftertaste, you can also pop your Perelel Pack in the freezer prior to taking the vitamins. You can see more tips & tricks here! (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) 

We also wanted to introduce you to our 1st Trimester Prenatal Vitamin Powder. We‚Äôd be happy to send you a pack to try on us! We specifically created this for the days you just aren't up for taking your full pill pack ‚Äî trust us, we've been there! This powder contains the essentials from your prenatal pack to cover your baseline needs in an easy, drinkable format that will help ease digestion and nausea. It just needs to be mixed with a cool liquid and taken on a full stomach. (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-vitamin-powder) 

If you‚Äôre interested in giving the 1st Trimester Prenatal Powder a try, we can send you one free of charge and pause your current subscription for 1 month. Please let us know how you would like to proceed. (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-vitamin-powder) 

Best, 
Team Perelel

subject: Refund for vitamin pack
body_text:
Hello, 

I‚Äôm four packs away from finishing the second trimester vitamin pack I purchased/delivered on (8/8) (#579045) 

That being said I want a refund for this purchase/product. 
About a week ago I began noticing the weirdest reaction to your vitamins. I began having a soapy taste in my mouth, anywhere I went it was as if soap was in the air and I could taste it. It would go back and forth between soapy and metallic taste. 
I drove my self crazy last week cleaning my house, airing out my house, switching laundry detergent, doing all the things trying to pinpoint this problem. Then concluded it must be the vitamins because that‚Äôs the only thing I had changed in my routine. 
That‚Äôs being said for the last several days I haven‚Äôt taken the vitamins and the taste has completely gone away, and went back to normal. 
I took the vitamins last night to see if the same thing occurred and about 30 minutes after taking them the symptom was back. I had the metal/soap taste in my mouth again. 

That being said I find this very concerning and caused me lots of mental stress as I feared something was majorly wrong. 
I noticed sadly the second month subscription of vitamins has already processed and shipped. 

Since I‚Äôm still in the 30 day window for my first month refund. I would like a refund. This side effect is so bothersome and a major issue. 

Thank you, 
Jaycie Kowolonek

subject: Order #614339
body_text:
Hello, 

I would like to cancel my subscription for the pre conception multivitamins. I have started this week for the past 5 days and have developed horrible cystic acne which I have never in my life had. Is there any type of refund as well where I can send the rest of the pack back. Unfortunately, the acne is not worth the vitamins for me. I was really hopeful that this would work out but unfortunately, they are not. 

Thank you for your time, 
Heather Burns

On Aug 16, 2024, at 2:24‚ÄØPM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hi Bella, 

Thanks for sharing your due date! This will ensure your subscription will automatically update alongside your due date so you receive the right pack for your trimester and into postpartum. 

As a heads up, your Perelel subscription follows the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG) defined trimesters: 
-1st Trimester: Week 0 through Week 13 
-2nd Trimester: Week 14 through Week 27 
-3rd Trimester: Week 28 through Week 40+ 

While the timing of when you start your vitamins with us doesn't always exactly align with your trimester, rest assured all of our packs will keep your needs covered during any overlap weeks! 

Want to connect with moms with a similar due date? Join our Geneva group now! (https://app.geneva.com/invite/997e7178-3982-4480-811f-252001048727) 

Feel free to let us know if you have any additional questions or see more FAQs here :) (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Fri, Aug 16, 2024, at 06:17 PM, Isabella Stuijfzand < stuijfzandeducation@gmail.com> wrote: (mailto:stuijfzandeducation@gmail.com) 
Thank you! 
Due date is 4/22/2025 

Will do thank you! 

On Fri, Aug 16, 2024, at 05:07 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hi Bella, 

Congratulations!! :) We have updated your subscription to the 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack. We'd love to collect your due date here so your subscription will automatically update alongside your pregnancy without any changes needed on your side! (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack) Could you kindly share your current due date so we can add this to your account? 

So you don't go a day without pills, we recommend taking your Conception Support Pack until you receive your next order of the (https://perelelhealth.com/products/conception-support-pack) 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack. However, we do suggest to stop taking the CoQ10 supplement in the pack, which is the orange capsule (seen (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack) here). Although there is no reason to think that CoQ10 is unsafe during pregnancy, most women do not need to continue it once pregnant. Your (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/our-vitamin-packs) 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack is now set to ship on (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack) 09/28/2024. Please let us know if you would like us to process the order at an earlier date! 

We know the early days of pregnancy can be plagued by nausea which can of course be made worse by a new supplement routine. Remember to always take your vitamins on a full stomach and with a full glass of water! Some customers find taking before bed and even popping their pack in the freezer before taking can help eliminate any lingering smells or tastes - you can see more tips & tricks here! Also, our medical co-founder, Dr. Bayati, loves how our packs allow her particularly sick patients to cover their baseline needs on days when they cannot stomach the full pack (or anything at all!) by taking only the smaller white folate pill! We also recommend (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) this article, which highlights what foods to eat in the 1st Trimester and can be very helpful when navigating this journey! (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/food-to-eat-in-first-trimester-of-pregnancy) 

You can also check out our free Label Checker online to check your other ingestible + topical products to ensure they are pregnancy safe. Additionally, we wanted to invite you to our (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/unclean15) Geneva group to connect with other women who are in the same trimester as you to ask any and all questions! (https://app.geneva.com/invite/997e7178-3982-4480-811f-252001048727) 

Best, 
Team Perelel

Thank you for reaching out to Perelel! We have received your email and our customer support team will be reaching out to assist you shortly. Our business hours are Monday through Friday from 9 am to 5 pm PST. Please allow 1 to 2 business days for someone from our team to get back to you. body_text:
Hi there, 

I‚Äôm just checking in because I saw that I was only refunded a portion of this order. I assume because typically shipping is not included in the refund, however I did not pay an initial shipping fee so should be refunded in full. Please advise. Thank you! 

Sent from my iPhone 
On Aug 23, 2024, at 10:51‚ÄØAM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hello Megan, 

Thank you for letting us know! That's a great idea! 

We're always happy to help! Feel free to let us know if there is anything else we can help with! 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Thu, Aug 22, 2024, at 04:07 PM, Megan Snyder Lynch < megansnyderlynch@gmail.com> wrote: (mailto:megansnyderlynch@gmail.com) 
Thank you so much for your response. I filled out the survey just a moment ago--please let me know if you did not receive and let me know if there is anything else you need from me. I will surely find a friend who can use these supplements and hopefully feel wonderful while taking them. :) 

I appreciate your help. Thanks again! 

On Thu, Aug 22, 2024, at 03:52 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hi Megan, 

We're so sorry to hear this! We have not heard this before, but every body is different. We suggest you speak with your doctor about your specific concerns. 

We would be happy to provide a refund for your first pack in order #532860 less the cost of shipping. Could you kindly complete this short survey to process your request? Once completed, we will go ahead with your refund. You should see this come back on your method of payment within 5-7 business days. (https://forms.gle/WNnSkKDHTtyY4XKx8) You do not need to return your unfinished Perelel Pack to us. 

Additionally, we canceled your subscription so you will not be charged for any future orders. 

Let us know if there is anything else we can help you with! 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Thu, Aug 22, 2024, at 01:56 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hello Megan, 

Thank you for reaching out to Perelel! We have received your email and our customer support team will be reaching out to assist you shortly. Our business hours are Monday through Friday from 9 am to 5 pm PST. Please allow 1 to 2 business days for someone from our team to get back to you. We'll do our best to reply to your email as quickly as possible. 

In the meantime, be sure to check out our FAQ page for help with general inquiries, managing your subscription, shipping and returns. (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Thank you for your patience! 

On Thu, Aug 22, 2024, at 01:55 PM, Megan Snyder Lynch < megansnyderlynch@gmail.com> wrote: (mailto:megansnyderlynch@gmail.com) 
Good morning. Have you had any reports of side effects for this prenatal? I just finally started these and I was so excited to give them a try. I had been using the Sakara prenatals for years and recently took a break from prenatals altogether but decided to get back on them as we are trying to conceive again (I know you have wonderful reviews!). I had very high hopes for these but seems I am having some extreme anxiety symptoms when taking them. I've only taken 10 packets (at most) so far but seem to be having this adverse reaction after taking them. Is there anything you recommend or is there anything you can do to rectify this? I know they are not re-sellable but I'd be happy to return the remaining packs (like I said I've only taken a handful), if possible. 

Thank you for your help and please do let me know if this is something you've heard as a side effect--or maybe I'm just an anomaly! 

Thanks!

subject: Order #621290
body_text:
Hello!

I am so sorry to write this but I‚Äôve tried taking your prenatal for two days (freezing the packs before hand because of the smell and taking them with food and right before bed both times) and I threw up profusely both times. I am not one who is easily disgusted but the smell of these is so bad that I cannot continue to take them. I feel like they made me/my body smell like them as well. Am I able to return these asap?

I apologize as I was really hoping these would work for me. The last time I threw up was so bad that i‚Äôm terrified of the pills and the smell now. Unfortunately these will not work for me.

Thank you so much for your understanding 

Amanda Ambriz

subject: Question about product
body_text:
Hi, 

I have been taking your prenatal (first trimester) for about 2 1/2 weeks now. I just wanted to email you and let you know that while I think the ingredients your prenatal offers is probably one of the better on the markets, it is really hard to swallow your pill without gagging / almost vomiting. I don‚Äôt have morning sickness (and I didn‚Äôt have it with my first child either) but your pills smell so fishy that just opening the package is hard to handle. What‚Äôs really interesting is that the EPA + DHA pill is the only one that doesn‚Äôt taste fishy. Have you ever given any thought to separately packaging the EPA + DHA pill? I‚Äôm thinking the fishiness of the other 4 pills is coming from being in the same packet as the fish oil pill. Just thought I would write you as I don‚Äôt know if you get the same feedback from other customers. Thanks for listening. 

Thank you, 
Pam Pierre 
(832) 752-9417 

--

subject: Return
body_text:
Hi, good morning. I recently received your line of products, and I was super excited to try them, but unfortunately, my stomach can't tolerate them. I become very nauseous or dislike¬†the taste. I tried to take the prenatal vitamins separately throughout the day. It helps a bit, but I think the folate really gets me super¬†nauseated, even just the smell of it. I further tried the greens and water hydration products, and I couldn't tolerate it, from the scent to the taste. 

Anyway, to get a refund, where do I send ¬†back¬†the products?¬†Thank you

body_text:
Hi perelel, 

I wanted to reach out as I have to cancel my upcoming subscriptions with your prenatal vitamins. The first trimester pack I have been unable to tolerate taking due to the fish smell and the fishy indigestion that follows. I was hoping to receive a refund for this within the 30 day satisfaction period. With the morning sickness I‚Äôm experiencing I am unable to get these pills down. 
The sleep supplement and greens are okay but I not using every day so I still have plenty left. 
I really appreciate your company and vitamins just unfortunately did not work out for me.

Thank you!
Allison

Is it possible to initiate any kind of return or refund given that two of the packs being taken? 

Warm regards,

body_text:
Hi there,

So I ordered these vitamins, received my first order today, and took my first pack of them earlier this afternoon after having a snack. Sadly, I‚Äôm just not going to be able to get through using them. I have horrible acid reflux (even before pregnancy) and these intensified my acid reflux tremendously. I did absolutely love the greens powder and I‚Äôm excited to try the probiotic tomorrow as I‚Äôve been looking for a good one, but the prenatals just aren‚Äôt going to be a good fit for me. 

Thank you so much, and again I‚Äôm so sorry for complaining about the product. Really had high hopes but with my gut issues it‚Äôs just too much on my stomach.

Lyndsey Chapman

subject: Fwd: Order #616827 confirmed
body_text:
Hi Perelel team, 

I ordered the Peri Support Pack after scouring the info to make sure it had no Ashwaganda because, like many other people I know, Ashwaganda gives me terrible anxiety and in fact I just switched from another company because they put Ashwaganda in their peri supplement. It isn‚Äôt listed anywhere in the description or anything but after several days of raging anxiety I was finally able to zoom in on the ingredients listed in terrible low resolution to see what I believe is the word Ashwaganda. I am frustrated to have spent $60 on yet another multivitamin/supplement pack that now I can only use a portion of. I would recommend you add clearer and more explicit ingredients to your product info because the photo viewed on a phone is illegible. If you see fit to refund this product, I would be grateful. 

Sadly I will need to cancel this subscription or I am really wasting some of what I‚Äôm paying for. Otherwise I really like what your company is doing but I can‚Äôt be up at night with a racing heart for hidden ingredients. Please do let me know if there are plans to have the other supplements available a la carte in the future. 

thank you, 
Ashley Kelemen

subject: Prenatal Vitamins
body_text:

Lauren Holland

body_text:
Hello, 

I purchased 2nd trimester prenatal vitamin pack. I did not like it as the smell of medicine are not good. I only had it on my first day and I threw up the meds as soon as I tried to take it. I would like to request a refund because I just used one from the pack. 

Thank you, 
Harnisha Patel

subject: Return Order
body_text:
Hello! 
I recently did my very first order with yall. I had ordered then Mens & Womens Daily Trio¬†pack, and also the Hormonal Balance Support Pills. 

While my husband and I are happy with our multi packs, I noticed I get extremely awful headaches that last all day from am - pm, when I take the hormonal pills (and I am someone who never gets headaches) 

I‚Äôve tested the pills out, and noticed if I take the Hormonal Support with the Daily Trio, or even without the Daily Trio pack - I still get awful headaches. 

But then when I‚Äôve tested taking the daily trio pack for 1 day with out the Hormonal support pills - then I get no headaches. 
How can I go about returning the Hormonal Support pills? 
My order number is #606251 My Name is Jordan Nolte 
Email: Jordan.tarnowski@yahoo.com (mailto:Jordan.tarnowski@yahoo.com) 
Thank you! Jordan

subject: Recent Order - Honest Feedback
body_text:
Hello, 

I am writing you regarding my order ORDER NO.¬†#626182 
I recently found out I was pregnant with baby #4 I have been a loyal customer to Ritual supplements since 2019 and have enjoyed their products. Through all 3 of my prior pregnancies I have thankfully never experienced any intense nausea and the only minor symptom I experienced in all of my first trimesters were mild food aversions but by no ¬†means have I ever experienced any vomiting. 

I wanted to share my honest experience with your product as it was not a good fit for me. 

What initially drew me to your product is I LOVE the idea that the supplements change through the pregnancy. I love your mission statement, how your products were founded and all the support with doctors for your products. 

Even though I had zero issue with Ritual I was very excited to try this product line for my 4th pregnancy. 

I just found out I was pregnant with baby #4 at 7 weeks pregnant I quickly ordered the first trimester box and it showed up yesterday. I excitedly opened up the packet today and took my first packet. I followed the instructions to take with a large glass of water and some food which I did. 

IMMEDIATELY when I put the pills in my mouth I could taste the ‚Äòvitamin‚Äô taste I took them in pairs and each time I slightly gagged. Merely due to the taste. 

Shortly after finishing my cup of water I started slightly gaging at the left over taste of vitamin I had. 

Any time I burped I experienced this rush of intense flush as I could feel me started to gag. Within 10-15 minutes of taking the vitamins I began gagging so intensely I was holding back vomit. 

Shortly after I spent the next 20 minutes vomitting everything I had just consumed. 

A pregnancy symptom I have NEVER experienced. Honestly I had such a negative association with the taste of the pills today that I can‚Äôt even imagine taking these pills one more time. 

The only thing I can suggest that would make me want to even attempt to try them again is if you offered a flavor/essence which ritual has. 

My ritual pills have always had an option to have a citrus or mint essence to their pills which have always made taking their pills effortless. 

So I just wanted to give my honest feedback and experience. Not sure if there‚Äôs anything I can do with the remaining 29 packets that I have but I will surely not be taking them and I‚Äôm very sad that this product did not work for me as I wanted to love these products. 

Sincerely, 

Callie 
Sent from my iPhone

body_text:
Good afternoon! 

I unfortunately need to cancel my subscription! I really wish these vitamins worked for me they are great didn‚Äôt make me nauseous or give me reflux! Unfortunately, something in them makes my face breakout. I am super sensitive to supplements and foods. 

When we are expecting I will give the 1st trimester supplements a try! 

Thank you! 

Maddie

subject: Having aversion issues
body_text:
Hello!

So sorry to be a pain, but is there any chance you have mint-flavored capsule options available for the prenatal packs? I‚Äôve been attempting to take the first trimester packs and the smell/taste of them makes me so nauseated that I have skipped many days due to their scent. After I take them, the smell even comes back up in burps and makes my nauseated again. My customer ID is EHE1BQCZ.

Sorry again for the trouble!

Petya Grozeva

subject: Fish Oil Capsules
body_text:
It appears to be more than just a smell and that they have actually gone rancid. They have also spoiled the taste and smell of the other vitamins in the packet. They make us both feel sick while taking. Is there any way to process a partial refund for my most recent order as the quality is definitely less than satisfactory. 

On Wed, Aug 28, 2024 at 9:05‚ÄØPM Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 

Hi Christina, 

Thank you for reaching out! Unfortunately, the smell is a side effect of natural vitamins, which can smell a bit.. natural! We rely on peppermint leaf powder to neutralize these smells, but with any natural ingredient, there can be fluctuations in the potency in each batch. We also avoided sugars, harmful additives, and fillers in our formulations which are often used to completely mask tastes or smells. We've done our best to create a product that is both tolerable and clean! Please see some tips and tricks in this article when adjusting to natural vitamins‚Äî Your Complete Guide to Taking All Natural Supplements. (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) 

Feel free to let us know if there is anything else we can help with in the meantime! 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Wed, Aug 28, 2024, at 03:10 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hello Christina, 

Thank you for reaching out to Perelel! We have received your email and our customer support team will be reaching out to assist you shortly. Our business hours are Monday through Friday from 9 am to 5 pm PST. Please allow 1 to 2 business days for someone from our team to get back to you. We'll do our best to reply to your email as quickly as possible. 

In the meantime, be sure to check out our FAQ page for help with general inquiries, managing your subscription, shipping and returns. (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Thank you for your patience!

subject: Vitamin consumption
body_text:
Good morning, 

I was reaching out because I wanted some clarification and advice. I stumbled across your website a few months back and as a holistic nutritionist myself, I love your approach. My husband and I are trying to conceive, and because your vitamins are personalized for every stage, I've been taking the conception support pack. However, I've found it hard to keep up with taking the pills daily. The smell threw me off when I first started taking them, but it's the fishy burps that occur throughout the day that have made consumption difficult. I‚Äôve read through the webpage that provides tips on taking natural vitamins and I've tried taking them with meals (during or after) and lots of water but I still have the same experience. On your webpage, it mentions you can take them right before bed. However, on the pouch, it says to take it with a meal. I suppose I'm asking if the absorption will be affected if I take them a few hours after my dinner meal and right before I go to bed. After thorough research, I applaud the quality of your products and I don't want to switch, but I find myself skipping my vitamins simply to avoid those constant fishy burps. 

I apologize for the long drawn-out explanation but look forward to hearing from you soon. 

Kind regards, 
Kimberly T

subject: Request for Refund of First 1st Trimester Vitamin Pack
body_text:
Dear Perelel Support Team, 
I hope this message finds you well. I am a long-time subscriber and have always enjoyed your women's multivitamin packs, which I took alongside another company's prenatal while trying to get pregnant. When I found out I was pregnant last month, I was excited to switch to your 1st Trimester vitamin packs. However, I am unfortunately struggling with severe morning sickness, and I‚Äôve found that the taste and smell of the 1st Trimester vitamin packs is simply too strong for me to keep down. 
I recently received Order #618814 on September 3rd, and while the packaging is still sealed and unopened, I don't believe I‚Äôll be able to use them. I saw in your FAQ that you have a guaranteed happiness policy, and I would love to switch back to your women‚Äôs multivitamin packs and find another prenatal solution that works for me. 
Please let me know if I can return the latest shipment to you for a refund or exchange it for the women's multivitamin packs instead. I truly appreciate your help and look forward to continuing with Perelel! 
Thank you in advance for your understanding. 
Best regards, 
Victoria Eardley --
tags: order/exchange, general-product/product, complaint/nausea, WTR1-P, complaint-date/2024-09-15, #618814, internal/log

subject: Package in the heat
body_text:
Hi, 

Is it possible to add an ice pack system with my next order please? It‚Äôs still so hot in texas just making sure it‚Äôs not getting too hot. 
And also, it is possible for The delivery not to be in the mail box? Font door is perfect. That would be so helpful üôèüôè thank you! 

Pascaline Thomas 

Sent from my iPhone 
On Aug 20, 2024, at 6:32‚ÄØPM, Pascaline Thomas <pascaline86@gmail.com> wrote: 
Thank you so much for your words, and updating the subscription! 

Pascaline 

Sent from my iPhone 
On Aug 20, 2024, at 6:30‚ÄØPM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hi Pascaline, 

We're so sorry to hear of your loss and our hearts are with you and your family. We went ahead and updated your subscription to the Conception Support Pack and processed a new order. It will be on its way to you shortly! (https://perelelhealth.com/products/conception-support-pack) 

In the meantime, we're here for you should you need anything else. 

With love, 
Team Perelel 

On Tue, Aug 20, 2024, at 09:31 PM, Pascaline Thomas < pascaline86@gmail.com> wrote: (mailto:pascaline86@gmail.com) 
Hi, 

Thanks again for sending a new 1st trimester package. 
Unfortunately- I miscarried two days ago. 
I was wondering if I could adjust the subscription and switch it to the ‚Äúconception‚Äù package. And when I get pregnant again I‚Äôll be able to use that 1st trimester pack and I‚Äôll switch back to the pregnancy subscription. 

So I‚Äôd like to order a conception pack and get enrolled please. 

Thank you for understanding. 

Pascaline 

On Fri, Aug 16, 2024, at 01:13 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hi Pascaline, 

Oh no, we're so sorry this happened to you! We don't believe it should be harmful for a short period of time, but in general, don't recommend keeping them in extreme heat and always recommend a cool dry place to store them. 

If you'd prefer, we are happy to issue a replacement order at 50% off with our temperature-controlled packaging. :) Please let us know how you'd like to proceed! 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Fri, Aug 16, 2024, at 12:56 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hello Pascaline, 

Thank you for reaching out to Perelel! We have received your email and our customer support team will be reaching out to assist you shortly. Our business hours are Monday through Friday from 9 am to 5 pm PST. Please allow 1 to 2 business days for someone from our team to get back to you. We'll do our best to reply to your email as quickly as possible. 

In the meantime, be sure to check out our FAQ page for help with general inquiries, managing your subscription, shipping and returns. (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Thank you for your patience!

Hi,  I received my 1st prenatal pack yesterday in my mailbox around 1:50pm. The package was supposed to arrive today so I didn't really check the status / and the mailbox until today. I live in Texas and the temperatures are above 102 degres. Which means the package sat in an extremely hot mailbox all afternoon. I doubt this is any safe for me to use? Any insights on this?  Thank you!  Pascaline

subject: Partial Subscription Cancelation
body_text:
Hi team, 

I was connect with someone on chat but unfortunately it wasn‚Äôt the most helpful. 

I currently have two active subscriptions. I would like to keep the subscription for the prenatal vitamins going into my second trimester. However, I would like to cancel the subscription for the synbiotic greens powder.

I would like to say the first trimester prenatal vitamins were very helpful. The smell and taste of the vitamin was a little hard to put down, but was worth the effort since it helped with my symptoms. This is why I am open to trying the second trimester prenatal pack. The flavor of the green powder, however did not sit well with me. I‚Äôm sure it is a great product, but it is something I am going to have to pass on for the time being.

Thank you for your product, and please let me know if any additional information is needed.

Best regards, 
Monica

subject: Order #631976
body_text:
Hello - I am reaching out to inquire about a refund on the order I recently received #631976. I have taken the prenatals for 3 days now and they really are much too difficult for me to bare, there‚Äôs no way I could manage to continue these for my entire second trimester or even the full month. I was switching over from another brand that had me taking 8 pills a day, and I thought these would be easier but the core prenatal pills truly smell horrible and the taste lingers in my mouth + causes me to burp for HOURS afterward bringing up the taste over and over. :( I read a lot of comments in online threads and some said to try freezing the pack for 30 minutes to and hour, however I didn‚Äôt seem to have luck with this helping the issues. ¬†Thank you for helping me to resolve this and send back the items for a refund. 

Kindly 
Danielle

subject: Question
body_text:
Hello! 

I ordered the Perelel conception support pack and I just got into it but I was going to be traveling so I wanted to put them into my pill box that I have my other meds/vitamins in. I poured 7 packs in and within minutes the smell was so terrible. Every time I walked into the bathroom for the next hour, the smell made me feel so nauseous. I ended up having to take all of my pils out and wash the container. Then I put them in a ziplock bag and put them in my suit case and the same thing happened. My car smells bad now too. I‚Äôm wondering if this is normal? Do you offer a scented kind so that the smell isn‚Äôt so bad? I honestly don‚Äôt know if I can take these because of the smell and I‚Äôm so bummed about that because I really liked the different packs. 

Let me know if this is a common issue, if there is any way to resolve etc. 

Thank you! 
Jenna Bates 

Order # 625205

subject: Smells like farts
body_text:
Hi there!

For my second trimester I had switched from a natural/organic prenatal to your supplement pack after reading all the wonderful things about the product.

I have tried freezing the pack and taking it with dinner before bed. I‚Äôve tried taking it with thicker drinks, all sorts of things. I am used to natural vitamin smells but this one tops them all.

It smells like someone sprayed fart spray in the packet. After taking them, if I burp, it tastes like I‚Äôm eating a fart. All day long. It is absolutely horrible. 

While your product offers all sorts of great benefits, the smell is unbearable. Is there anything that can be done or any suggestions?

Thank you kindly,
Christine

subject: Subscription cancellation and refund
body_text:
Good afternoon, 
 
My name is Nicole O'Dea. I started a subscription of the conception support a few weeks ago and have been taking the pills for a week. I was very happy with the evidence-based approach behind this pill set and really wanted to use it. However, as much as I
 wanted it to a good fit, I'm finding that they are not sitting well with me. Unfortunately, I don't think it's the right fit for me. Is it possible to cancel my subscription and get a refund? 
 
Thanks! 
Nicole 
 
 
 Nicole O‚ÄôDea, PhD Project Manager Tufts Interdisciplinary Evaluation Research (TIER) pronouns: she/her/hers

subject: Refund for Order #621320
body_text:
Hi there, 

I recently received my first order of the Conception Support Pack on 9/6/24 and would like to request a refund. Unfortunately I cannot stomach the smell/taste of the vitamins, even after trying multiple of the recommendations suggested by Perelel to help with that. There's an extremely potent odor as soon as I open the pack, even if I put them in the freezer, and I get extremely nauseous¬†even thinking about taking them. 

Would it be possible to receive a refund for the pack, as I am unable to take them? 

Also please let me know¬†if there are options for donating the vitamins to others who may be able to take them. 

Thank you for the support, 
Katie Franklin

subject: Extreme nausea and vomiting after starting Perelel
body_text:
Hello team, 

I started Perelel after my 8w appointment and currently am on the second trimester pack. 
Both the times, during the first and the second trimester packs, I have been experiencing extreme nausea and vomiting. 
I ignored it during my first but it's not getting any better. 
I also put the pack in the freezer for an hour before consuming, take it with a full stomach, before bed and nothing seems to help. 
The smell is triggering my nausea quite a lot. 

I have paused my subscription for now but would like to understand the policy around money back as this prenatal is definitely not working for me. 

Looking¬†forward to hearing from you. 

Thank you.

subject: Return /exchange/refund request
body_text:
Hello Perelel, 
I purchased 2 packages of your prenatal vitamins for first trimester. Unfortunately, I wasn't able to consume them during my first months, and even now I just can't. Your vitamins have a taste, a very difficult to swallow smell and taste. Even after taking them with water, juice and delicious food, I cannot. If I drink it next to someone else, they also comment on the strong smell. I keep tasting them for hours after. 
One packet is still sealed, I never opened the box because I purchased 2 together. 
Can I please exchange them for something else? 

Thank you, 
Karol

When I changed to the second trimester pack, I‚Äôve had diarrhea ever since‚Ä¶ was there a probiotic in the first and not the second? I‚Äôm trying to see if there is a difference between the packs. Thanks for your help. 

Noel Clarke

On Jul 25, 2024, at 9:08 PM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hi Noel, 

Your next order for the 2nd Trimester Prenatal Pack and the Daily Iron Ease will be processed on 08/03/2024. Feel free to let us know if you end up needing this sooner or pushed back to a later date! 

After an order is placed, please allow 1 day for processing at our warehouse, and then 3-7 business days for delivery. We appreciate your patience with us as we rely on our partners to deliver packages as quickly and safely as possible. 

Let us know if you have any additional questions or please check out additional FAQs here! (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq)

Hi! 

I wanted to see if you can share expected shipment date for my second pack. I am leaving for vacation this Sunday, and do not return until 8/3 so I wanna make sure I am home to get it and it doesn‚Äôt sit in the mailbox. Thank you! 

On Thu, Jul 11, 2024, at 03:34 AM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hi Noel, 

Thanks for sharing your due date! This will ensure your subscription will automatically update alongside your due date so you receive the right pack for your trimester and into postpartum. 

As a heads up, your Perelel subscription follows the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG) defined trimesters: 
-1st Trimester: Week 0 through Week 13 
-2nd Trimester: Week 14 through Week 27 
-3rd Trimester: Week 28 through Week 40+ 

While the timing of when you start your vitamins with us doesn't always exactly align with your trimester, rest assured all of our packs will keep your needs covered during any overlap weeks! 

Want to connect with moms with a similar due date? Join our Geneva group now! (https://app.geneva.com/invite/997e7178-3982-4480-811f-252001048727) 

Feel free to let us know if you have any additional questions or see more FAQs here :) (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Thu, Jul 11, 2024, at 01:53 AM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hello Noel, 

Thank you for reaching out to Perelel! We have received your email and our customer support team will be reaching out to assist you shortly. Our business hours are Monday through Friday from 9 am to 5 pm PST. Please allow 1 to 2 business days for someone from our team to get back to you. We'll do our best to reply to your email as quickly as possible. 

In the meantime, be sure to check out our FAQ page for help with general inquiries, managing your subscription, shipping and returns. (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Thank you for your patience!

Thank you,
Inah

subject: Subscription ASAP
body_text:
Hi,

I have a subscription for your prenatal packs. This was delivered on Friday (9/20). I am currently out of my prenatal packs and really need a new one (second trimester) sent to me ASAP. subject: Could not use the product
body_text:
Hello I ordered 2nd trimester Prenatal Pack and I need to be honest. I hated it everything about it. Is it possible for the refund? 
My order number is ORDER NO.¬†#631839 

To describe what I did not like about it- 
1. Pill size - Just too big!!! Even I feel past my nausea I still gaged trying to swallow all the pills. 
2. SMELL!!! when you open the packet it smells like dog food or dried bones/meat. It smells horrible and I start to gag from it. 
3. When I actually swallow the pills I have horrible burps with that smell which makes me feel nauseous again and I truly can‚Äôt enjoy them. 

I bet the ingredients are good, but to get them in my body. I just can‚Äôt and it breaks my heart that I needed to pay almost 70$ for them. I haven‚Äôt made public feedback.. just thought to email directly. 

Thank you and look forward to hear back! 

Best, 
Ieva Ferdman

body_text:
Hi! I hope all is well.
I wanted to cancel my subscription because I cannot keep these supplements down. I wanted to love them so badly but they smell and taste so horrendous. Please let me know. Thank you so much 
Sarah

subject: Hydration Powder
body_text:
Hello - I received my order a few mornings ago of the cellular hydration powder order#641207. I'm 9 months postpartum and bought this because my skin has been feeling dry and thought this could help me feel refreshed and hydrated. I've taken it the past 2 mornings and my face is starting break out - i've never had breakouts on this cheek before and this is the only new thing i've added to my routine.

I'm afraid to keep taking it because I don't want my skin to get worse. Is there any way of getting a refund?

Meghan

subject: Hormonal Balance Support Question
body_text:
Hi there! 

I have two inquiries- 

1) I had skipped this most recent delivery of the supplement, but it shipped anyways. I haven‚Äôt finished the last bottle- can I return this one for a refund? 

2) I started taking this at the beginning of this most recent cycle for me. My cycles have usually been ~42 days long. I thought I had ovulated on CD21 for a 35 day cycle, but no sign of AF and my pregnant test was negative. Should I anticipate adverse effects like a longer-than-average cycle as my body acclimates? I‚Äôm pretty concerned and disheartened about this since my husband and I are trying to conceive. Otherwise, I have felt great taking this supplement (less bloat, stable energy/mood, minimal acne, higher libido) so I am quite confused and looking for answers. Any advice and insight is appreciated! 

Thank you so much! 
Megan Connolly

subject: Had to stop taking vitamins
body_text:
Hi there, 

I took your vitamins throughout my first and into my second trimester. Despite their foul smell (I understand this might be the choline?), I kept taking them and was quite ill throughout my entire pregnancy with lots of nausea. This is my third baby and I've never been sick with prior pregnancies so naturally I was confused. 

I finally considered it might be the Perelel vitamins and so I switched for a week to another brand. The difference was stark! No more nausea at all. That said, I haven't been taking the Perelels for a few weeks now and haven't opened my latest shipment. 

What can be done about this in addition to cancelling my subscription? 

Thank you so much for understanding! 
Amelia Cassar 
-- 
Amelia Cassar Lifestyle, Wedding & Corporate Photographer ameliacassarphoto.com

body_text:
Aloha, 

My name is Hailey! I just received my first order from Perelel and I‚Äôm super excited to start! I‚Äôve been on hormonal birth control for probably around 15 years due to my PCOS. Recently my boyfriend and I have been talking about starting a family and I want to be in the best position health wise to do so. I‚Äôve also just been very curious what my body is like without birth control. I‚Äôve been on it so long, I can‚Äôt really remember. 

I  just received my conception pack, hormonal balance support and probiotic in the mail today! I was wondering if you would recommend waiting to start until after my next period? And I also was hoping for some clarification on how to take the hormonal balance support‚Äîit says 2 pills 2 times a day. So does that mean four pills a day‚Äîtwo in the morning and two at night? And if so should I order two bottles at a time to last me the entire month? 

Mahalo, 
Hailey Ka‚Äôuhane

subject: No period since starting perelel
body_text:
Hi, I started the Perelel egg freeze support pack on day 2 of my cycle and I‚Äôm now on day 39 and have not had a period. I‚Äôve always had very regular 24-28 day cycles. Starting this supplement has been the only thing I‚Äôve done different. Is this normal? What ingredients does the supplement contain that would delay/stop menstruation? 

Thanks and I look forward to a reply,

Arminta 

Sent from my iPhone. Please forgive typos/short form!

Anastasia Askitis

Thank you. Carmela

I just canceled my subscription because I have tried 3x to take the prenatals and it got more challenging each time. The smell is really affecting me and by the third time it made me physically ill causing me to throw up multiple times. Unfortunately I cannot continue taking these as the smell is making me ill. I‚Äôd like to receive a refund as I am within my 30 days since ordering/receiving them. How do I go about this? Thank you! 

Ashley Butler

subject: Issues with prenatal supplements
body_text:
Hello, 

I ordered your first trimester prenatal pack. I started noticing some very serious side effects after taking them. Absolutely no physical or mental energy, slight depressive state, body aches and nausea/upset stomach. 
Of course I thought this was just my natural first trimester symptoms, in the beginning. 
Then day after day of feeling like absolute death I was getting suspicious that something might be up. 
So I skipped taking my prenatal and within 24 hours starting feeling like myself again. Day 2 and I‚Äôm not having any bad symptoms. 

This leads me to believe that something in the supplements is not reacting with me well at all. 
I will be discontinuing the prenatal and would like a refund, if possible.

Also I‚Äôd really like to know if this is something that has happened with other pregnant women taking your product?

Thank you,

Kat Traylor

Sent from my iPhone
tags: Side Effects, refund/30-day, WTR1-P, complaint-date/2024-09-30, cancel/do-not-like, internal/log, #641618, complaint/side-effects

subject: Side Effects
body_text:
Hi, 

I had a really bad reaction to taking my vitamins for the first time. I had a normal dinner around 8pm and took my first mom pack and first libido support pill at 8:45. By 10, I had horrible cramping in my stomach. From 10:30-11:30 I then had two bad bouts of diarrhea and vomiting at the same time. No one else in my house is sick so I really don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs what I had for dinner. 

As soon as I got it out of my system I felt fine. 

Have you heard of this strong of a reaction before? I‚Äôm quite scared to try again tonight.

Would love your thoughts. 

Thanks,
Jamie 
Sent from my iPhone

On Thursday, July 11, 2024, 11:38 AM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 
Hi Chelsi, 

Thank you for getting back to us! We went ahead and canceled your subscription. You will not be charged for any future orders. 
Unfortunately, the smell is a side effect of natural vitamins, which can smell a bit.. natural! We rely on peppermint leaf powder to neutralize these smells, but with any natural ingredient, there can be fluctuations in the potency in each batch. We also avoided sugars, harmful additives, and fillers in our formulations which are often used to completely mask tastes or smells. We've done our best to create a product that is both tolerable and clean! Please see some tips and tricks in this article when adjusting to natural vitamins‚Äî Your Complete Guide to Taking All Natural Supplements. (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) 

If you're ever open to giving us another try, we'd love to offer you a 15% discount using the code COMEBACK15 on your next order. 

Best, 
Team Perelel

subject: Prenatal Pill Issue
body_text:
Hello, 
I have been taking your TTC pills for a few months now. I have noticed that since I started I have been getting a crazy amount of hormonal acne all around my jaw line, shoulders, back. I cant remember it being this bad even in my teen years. Is this a side effect of your pills? I'm not sure what I should do :( I have been on the BC pill for a year so I don't think its coming off of that. The acne is really spirit crushing :( do you guys have anything to counter this or do I just need to try another prenatal? 

Thank you, 

Nicola Baldwin

subject: Re: So, what do you think?
body_text:
Hi perelel team, 

Just wanted to reach out to say my mom multi support pack has been making me feel sick. I started taking it for a 4-5 days in the recent postpartum and then stopped thinking maybe was my stomach. I recently re started taking it at 6 weeks postpartum to give it another try and the same is happening ü•≤ I can‚Äôt help but gag and if I force myself to take them will have lots of fishy hiccups that will make me feel sick. 

This never happened with other vitamins before, apart of one of your pregnancy vitamin batches. 

Would love to know if this is expected with the ingredients in your vitamins or if maybe I got a bad batch. I‚Äôve paused my subscription in the meantime.

subject: 3rd Trimester support order
body_text:
Hi, 

My name is Alayna Knudsen and I am a subscriber. I have used the conception pack and prenatals and am currently on my first 3rd trimester support pack. The order just came not long ago and I just finished my second trimester last box and opened this 3rd trimester box. I have taken one vitamin pack so far. And I grabbed the second one out of the box this morning and it is not filled correctly. Only one of the brown ish core prenatals has powder in it. The other is an empty opened capsule inside the sealed pack packaging and no powder visible in the daily pack. this is strange and has never happened to me before. My husband also takes the men‚Äôs support pack as well and neither of us have ever seen our 30 packs in the box not be complete. Is there anything you can do about this to help a loyal subscriber? I‚Äôll attach a picture below. 




Thank you, 

Alayna Knudsen 


Sent from my iPhone

subject: Refund order #628997
body_text:
Hi Perelel, 

I researched a bunch and was excited to find your product, but after taking your packs for about 10 days I found my self much sicker/more nauseous, and throwing up often. This is my 5th baby, I know these things are normal, but I had been feeling better this pregnancy than any of my others prior to taking Perelel. I don't think my body could take the smell, and throwing them up was a miserable experience. I stopped taking them Sept 25 and my nausea immediately improved and I haven't thrown up since. I believe they have great ingredients and I'm sad they didn't work out for me, but if I could get a refund that would be great. 

Thanks, 
Whitney
tags: complaint/smell, #628997, complaint/smell-taste, complaint/nausea, internal/log, WTR1-P, complaint-date/2024-10-05

subject: Order #657442
body_text:
Hello, 

I just received my first order of prenatal vitamins for my second trimester. While I was very excited to try Perelel after hearing great things about your other products, I've had a¬†less than satisfactory experience. Unfortunately¬†I'd like to request a return and refund. I was super excited to get my vitamins, and love the brand and packaging, but when I took my first set of pills, the smell and taste were so vile, I couldn't keep them down for longer than 20 minutes. I did have the pills on a fuller stomach, and while eating, as the packing recommends but I've honestly never had anything that tastes as awful. 

I thought I should keep trying to take them and that maybe I would adjust but that just doesn't¬†seem to be the case. On day 2 and 3, I changed the timing of when I took my vitamins to lunch time, so I could have them with my biggest meal, and sadly this hasn't¬†helped. 

Please let me know what I can do to return¬†the rest and get my money back. 

Thank you, 
Rebecca Hubbard

Thank you for your consideration.

Casey

subject: Return, refund and subscription cancelation
body_text:
Dear Perel Customer Service, 
I hope this message finds you well. I recently purchased your vitamins but, unfortunately, I have had a very unpleasant experience with them. Upon taking the first dose, I noticed that both the smell and taste were quite strong and unappealing. I did manage to take the initial dose, but it left me feeling nauseous for a few hours. 
Today, when I opened the package to take the vitamins again, I found myself unable to do so due to the same overwhelming taste and smell. Because of this, I would like to kindly request a return and refund for the product, as well as a cancellation of the subscription associated with this purchase. 
I appreciate your understanding and would prefer not to leave a public review, as I understand others may have different experiences with your product. Thank you for your assistance, and I look forward to your prompt response. 
Best regards, Nikola Phillips!

subject: 2nd trimester pack- extreme nausea & vomiting
body_text:
Hello! 

I have been taking your conception support pack and prenatal for years now. But I am very disappointed in the 2nd trimester support pack. Unfortunately, as women we tend to blame ourselves for when things don‚Äôt go right. As an example, morning sickness is just a right of passage. So I rightfully assumed the late night puking was just that, an unfortunate pregnancy symptom. 

After reaching out to friends for help, they have all pointed unfortunately in your direction, the perelel vitamin pack. The perelel vitamin has made them so nauseous, and stopping or switching seemed to immediately change this. I understand we are vulnerable to a lot of things making us nauseous, but it has occurred to me your vitamin might be causing an acute heightened reaction. It is for me. I trusted this product and it unfortunately let me down. 

So my ask- 
1. Explain that these ingredients might make you more nauseous vs. your non-nausea formula. 
2. Really really encourage this vitamin with a full stomach and not at night time. 
3. Contact support if symptoms continue. 

Thank you, 

Berkeley
tags: WTR2-P, replacement/courtesy, complaint-date/2024-10-11, #640772, siena-follow-needed, complaint/nausea, internal/log, assisted-by-siena

subject: Shipments not in line with when I run out of vitamins
body_text:
Good morning,

I am out of my vitamins. Usually I get a new shipment before I run out of the last batch. The tracking gives me two different dates- one says it will be delivered tomorrow 10/10 and one says Saturday which would be 10/12. 

Because of the timing, the vitamins will now be sitting outside in the warm weather for a long weekend, as I will not be able to receive them. I‚Äôm not sure how the timing of the shipments went off course, but this is quite frustrating and disappointing.

I‚Äôm considering canceling my subscription, as this is the second time something‚Äôs gone wrong with a shipment.

Roxanne

Sent from my iPhone

subject: Perelel Subscription
body_text:
Hi There, 

I was hoping someone could help me with my subscription/account. I recently signed up for a subscription through the website and totally messed something up. 

I saw it wasn't shipping for a month so I clicked a button that said send now and then it added another order. I then cancelled both of them thinking I could just start over, but the next day I received that my items had shipped. I thought it was a glitch in the system so I let it be. Decided to wait a couple days to go back into my account and add a new subscription. (I hope that makes sense ha) 

I was checking the mail and received two orders. Unfortunately they had been sitting in the hot sun/mailbox for 3 days prior to me knowing they were there. They smell horrible. I know they are natural but that were very potent. 

Basically, I'm wondering if it's safe to still take them since I paid for them and now have two months worth? 

Also can you tell me if I'm actually signed up for a subscription or do I need to go into my account and fix something? I do want to be subscribed as I'm pregnant and due June 8th. So I want to make sure I'm on track to receive the right packets. 

Sorry for the long email! 

Order #s 
659165 
659049 

Thank You!! 
Toni Smiley Moen 
Yahoo Mail: Search, Organize, Conquer (https://mail.onelink.me/107872968?pid=NativePlacement&c=Global_Acquisition_YMktg_315_EmailSignatureGrowth_YahooMail:Search,Organize,Conquer&af_sub1=Acquisition&af_sub2=Global_YMktg&af_sub3=&af_sub4=100000945&af_sub5=OrganizeConquer__Static_)

subject: Re: Checking in: How‚Äôs the morning sickness? ü§¢
body_text:
Unfortunately, I don‚Äôt have nausea until I take my Perelel prenatals. I‚Äôve tried everything; cooling them, taking them at night, taking one pill with a full glass of water with a large snack or meal. 

Within an hour, I go down and it‚Äôs debilitating. 

I‚Äôm not one to typically suffer from nausea so I wanted to share this feedback given the subject line. 

Hannah Dalpiaz

subject: Prenatal powder issue
body_text:
Hello,

I was recently pregnant in March but suffered a miscarriage in May so I had some leftover 1st trimester prenatal pills. I used them when I first found out of my recent pregnancy but then bought the powder as I‚Äôve suffered from a lot of nausea and sickness. Unfortunately the smell from the powder has been so overwhelming that I switched back to the pills.  Is there any way I can return the powders or can you repurpose the packets for someone else to use?

I‚Äôve tried to put them in smoothies, morning, afternoon and night and nothing works. Every time I try to drink it the smell makes me sick sadly. 

Thank you for taking the time to read this email.

Haley Brower
Sent from my iPhone

subject: Prenatal vitamins
body_text:
Hello 
I have taken your prenatal vitamins for several days now in the mid afternoon which has resulted with me having a massive migraine at the end of the day lasting all night until I take some sort of migraine medicine which is not a great thing to be taking during pregnancy. Do you have any thoughts why this would be causing me completely debilitating migraines? I was not ending my day with them before taking these vitamins. I do know I have a migraine trigger of cinnamon and nutmeg is either of those in there? Are there any other spices? Ginger might also be a trigger for me but I have not confirmed it at all. Is there anything you can do to help, any other vitamins you recommend that are still good with the right folate and b vitamins without all the extras? 
Thank you 
Christine Peek

body_text:
Hello, 

I wanted to inquire about a possible refund--I've taken this supplement four times and each time it's caused bad bloating and mild stomach cramps. I've taken maca for years and have tried other libido support so I'm not sure what's not meshing with this one--is the maca not gelatinized? I wanted to inquire about a refund for this--please let me know. Thank you! 
Brianna

subject: Postpartum kit
body_text:
Good morning, 

Reaching out regarding the mom support kit. It contains ashwagandha. Per some basic googling, this should be avoided for women who are breastfeeding‚Ä¶.please advise. I would like a refund as I will not be taking these anymore. I trusted Perelel throughout my entire pregnancy, but this seems like a huge oversight on your part. 
Thank you. 

Olivia

subject: Fwd: Thank you for your subscription - Perelel
body_text:
Hello Perelel team - I am writing to request a refund on the vitamins from the second delivery of my 2nd trimester subscription.¬† I am absolutely struggling to consume these vitamins, and they take everything I have not to throw them up as I take them.¬† Considering your audience is pregnant ladies that struggle with esophogial¬†issues, smell and taste, these vitamins are absolutely terrible.¬† I have no way of telling if they are helpful to my growing baby, but as the host of the baby I can tell you these are just awful.¬† Taking 5 putrid smelling pills is pure torture, and I just can't do it.¬† I fought through the first box, but mentally I am worn out and cannot proceed any further.¬† I have one unopened 30 day supply that I'd love to return please.¬† I'm happy this works for other women, but not for me.¬† Please help me with this refund. 

Respectfully, 
Lauren Boulier

subject: Questions
body_text:
Hello, 

I recently received your prenatal vitamins and started to take them. The smell and taste is pretty awful and I have very bad morning sickness I tried to freeze them and it didn‚Äôt help much. I am also burping the taste up pretty much for a couple hours after taking them and they are making me miserable. I know it‚Äôs probably just me and my specific pregnancy symptoms, but is there any why I could send them back and get a refund and cancel my subscription? 

Please let me know how to proceed, I apologize for even having to send this type of email but I just can‚Äôt take them. 

Kindly, 

Samantha Kevorkian

subject: Looking for return
body_text:
Hello,

I just received my second trimester pack and I am hoping to see about a return. I got the first trimester pack a while back but was extremely sick my first trimester and  the smell of the packs made me throw up. Now that I‚Äôm feeling much better, I tried to take the second trimester ones the last few days and each time become sick. I‚Äôm hoping to return the second trimester pack (I don‚Äôt believe I can for the first trimester pack). 

I‚Äôm very sad as I loved the idea I‚Äôd these the ingredients are wonderful! But I just cannot seem to stomach them at all. 

Thank you,
Rebekah

body_text:
Good Afternoon, 

I hope this email finds you well. I am writing concerning my subscription. Please advise. 

Thanks, 

Ann Jacobson

subject: Questions
body_text:
Hi I ordered a support pack that has not yet expired but I noticed the supplements taste a little different/strange than usual. I did order these in advance and opened them a few weeks after receiving them. I have taken a few packs already and the taste is not new to me. Was just wondering if you've heard of this before and if it's¬†safe to consume. 

Thanks! 

On Mon, May 6, 2024 at 11:28‚ÄØPM Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 

Hi Fara, 

Thanks for reaching out! We recommend the Conception Support Pack. All of the doctors on our Perelel panel recommend their patients start on the (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/our-panel) Conception Support Pack around 6 months prior to becoming pregnant. Our medical co-founder often recommends starting a whole year prior to help your body build up all its nutrient stores and be best prepared to support a pregnancy, which you can read more about (https://perelelhealth.com/products/conception-support-pack?_pos=1&_sid=52817ea46&_ss=r) here! (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/when-to-take-prenatal-vitamins-for-pregnancy?_pos=1&_sid=017adda6a&_ss=r) 

Our Omega does contain gelatin. Our gelatin source is bovine. 

For any specific concerns, however, we do recommend you speak to your doctor for your individual needs! 

Let us know if you have any additional questions or check out more FAQs here! (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Tue, May 07, 2024, at 03:04 AM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hello Fara, 

Thank you for reaching out to Perelel! We have received your email and our customer support team will be reaching out to assist you shortly. Our business hours are Monday through Friday from 9 am to 5 pm PST. Please allow 1 to 2 business days for someone from our team to get back to you. We'll do our best to reply to your email as quickly as possible. 

In the meantime, be sure to check out our FAQ page for help with general inquiries, managing your subscription, shipping and returns. (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Thank you for your patience!

subject: Returning product due to allergy

subject: Prenatal - first trimester
body_text:
Hello,

My name is Rachael I am currently 7 weeks pregnant and just starting my journey in pregnancy. I did a lot of research for a good prenatal and recently switched over to your prenatal first trimester pack as I loved the story and the ingredients. Unfortunately my stomach says otherwise. I have taken them for about 3 days now and I cannot stomach the pills. As soon as I take them they come right back up. I hate to do this to you but being these are so expensive, I only have just started the package, and I cannot keep them down is there anyway to send them back for a refund?

My order number was #667349

I appreciate everything you are doing and continue to support what you believe in just hoping you can help me out as it was just not the one for me. 

Thank You,
Rachael
tags: internal/log, cancel/do-not-like, refund/30-day, WTR1-P, product-sensitivity/nausea, complaint-date/2024-10-17, #667349

subject: Refund for order #657394
body_text:

I ordered the first trimester pack and tried them for weeks, but ufortunately, could not tolerate the smell and taste of the pills, especially while nauseous in my first trimester. I tried freezing and taking at night as well. I think I‚Äôm better off with a different brand. 

I cancelled my subscription and wanted to inquire about a refund for the first month of product. My order number was #657394. Please let me know what else you need in order to process the refund. 

Thank you,
Amber Kaplan

subject: Questions about Hormonal Balance Support
body_text:
Hi 

I have struggled with¬†hormonal acne since I was 15, I'm now 44. Ive tried everything¬†and nothing¬†really works. I took the Clear Stem Root cause analysis blood test through Rupa labs and it seems I have blood sugar issues, high A1C and liver issues in metabolizing my hormones and glucose. I've been active all my life and eat healthy, so that's not the issue. I wonder if Myo-Inositol and D-Chiro-Inositol would help my body balance blood sugar, and allow my liver to process glucose and my hormones better. 
I read the reviews but they were mostly about pregnancy, PCOS and regular periods- none of which I have issues with. So my question is about clearing up hormonal acne- will this supplement help me with this? 
Thank you! Leslie 
-- 
All the best, Leslie Holistic Psychotherapist www.alistica.com (http://www.alistica.com)

subject: 2nd Tri Prenatals
body_text:
Hello,

I recently ordered the 2nd trimester prenatal vitamins and tried to take them for the first time tonight. I immediately threw up due to the smell and taste of the vitamins. I previously took the conception support packs and liked those. I was hoping to like these too but there‚Äôs no way I will be able to take these and, unfortunately, I feel like I just wasted $50. I‚Äôm wondering if I can receive a refund or at least partial refund.

Thanks for your consideration,

Hannah

subject: Subscription
body_text:
Hello - I‚Äôd like to give the conception pack another try. Can you please sign me up for subscription pack with 15% off using comeback15? 

________________________________________ 
On Jul 23, 2024, at 1:55‚ÄØPM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hi Reeva, 

Thanks for confirming this! Sorry to hear that our Perelel Packs did not work out for you. We went ahead and canceled your subscription, so you will not be charged for any future orders. 
Unfortunately, the smell is a side effect of natural vitamins, which can smell a bit.. natural! We rely on peppermint leaf powder to neutralize these smells, but with any natural ingredient, there can be fluctuations in the potency in each batch. We also avoided sugars, harmful additives, and fillers in our formulations which are often used to completely mask tastes or smells. We've done our best to create a product that is both tolerable and clean! Please see some tips and tricks in this article when adjusting to natural vitamins‚Äî Your Complete Guide to Taking All Natural Supplements. (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) 

If you're ever open to giving us another try, we'd love to offer you a 15% discount using the code COMEBACK15 on your next order. 

Best, 
Team Perelel
