subject: Concern Regarding the Smell of First Trimester Prenatal Vitamins
body_text:
Dear Perelel Team, 
I hope this message finds you well! I wanted to start by saying how much I love your product. The tailored prenatal vitamin packs for each trimester have been a game-changer for me, and I especially appreciate how clean and well-reviewed your vitamins are. I‚Äôm currently in my first trimester and was so excited to start using your vitamins to support my pregnancy journey. 
However, I‚Äôve run into a bit of a challenge. When I received my first-trimester pack, I noticed that the vitamins had an extremely strong and unpleasant smell. I‚Äôve experienced stinky vitamins before and understand that sometimes the best products have a bit of a smell, but this one has been particularly difficult for me, especially given my heightened sensitivity during pregnancy. 
I live in Tampa, Florida, and I can‚Äôt help but wonder if the heat during delivery may have affected the vitamins. I truly want to continue using your product throughout my pregnancy, but the smell has been quite overwhelming. I‚Äôd love to know if this is a normal experience or if there may have been an issue with the shipping conditions in my case. 
Thank you so much for your time and understanding. I look forward to your guidance on how to proceed, as I‚Äôd love to continue my subscription with Perelel. 
Warm regards, 
Stephanie
tags: internal/log, complaint/smell-taste, WTR1-P, other/fishy, product-sensitivity/smell-taste, assisted-by-siena, complaint-date/2024-10-21, replacement/courtesy

subject: Tips for taking perelel
body_text:
Hello,

I am having a hard time taking the egg freezing packet and fertility support. The taste and smell is so strong that I dreaded taking them. I gave up after a week and went back to my regular prenatal. Any tips on how to take them so it‚Äôs easier to swallow? Since they are pricey, I really don‚Äôt want to throw them away. Thank you!

Regards
Mary Her

Sent from my iPhone

subject: First Trimester Pills
body_text:
Hi! 

My name is Alisa Zayas and I have a few subscriptions to Perelel for different products (sleep aid, electrolytes, green powder, and the 1st trimester pills as I recently found out I am pregnant - approx 6 weeks along at this time). I began taking the 1st trimester pills on Oct 8th or 9th, and was getting super intense nausea and vomiting from them. I stopped taking them this past Saturday (Oct 19th), and the nausea/vomiting has subsided, but I am concerned that I am not taking my prenatal vitamins anymore. I have a simple CVS brand as well, but was wondering if I could receive either a refund for the pills or perhaps try to powder as an alternative? Please advise. 

Thank you so much for your help with this, 
Alisa
tags: internal/log, cancel/do-not-like, complaint/nausea, refund/30-day, WTR1-P, complaint-date/2024-10-21, #663126, complaint- date/ 2024 -10-21

subject: Dissatisfied with product
body_text:
Hi there, 

I have tried to use the synbiotic greens powder (order #660360). I have used AG1 and another greens powder and this one tastes very bad. I was hoping to enjoy this one while pregnant but the taste is truly not good. I cannot use this and I feel like I have just wasted money. 

Can I get a refund or something? Is sending it back an option? I have probably taken 3 scoops out of it. 

Thank you, 
Brooke
tags: internal/log, complaint/smell-taste, cancel/do-not-like, refund/30-day, WGRN-B, complaint/taste, complaint-date/2024-10-21, #660360

subject: Return Request
body_text:
Hello, 

I‚Äôve almost finished the first trimester pack of prenatal vitamins. I would like to return my unopened second trimester pack. 

My order number was 
638632 

The smell/taste/aftertaste of the Perelel vitamins is so bad that it has caused me to throw up more than once. I had some nausea before starting the pills, but I never came close to throwing up. Before I started taking Perelel‚Äôs 5 pill multivitamin pack, I was taking 7 larger pills. I wasn‚Äôt enjoying taking 7, but they did not smell like death, and they never made me throw up. 
I‚Äôm sorry this is so dramatic, but opening¬†the little packs and smelling the disgusting smell, trying to swallow them, and then tasting them for the next five hours whenever I burp has been the grossest part of my pregnancy so far. I agree with a review I read last week (that was otherwise very positive!) that said it is inane to include an anti-nausea pill in a pack of pills that smells so disgusting. I love horses and the smell of stables is nostalgic to me, but these pills taste like actual horse poop, and I can‚Äôt deal with it anymore.¬†I imagine the contents are high quality,¬†but it is truly nauseating to try to ingest these pills. 

I‚Äôm in my second trimester now, and I just have to switch to something that does not smell like death. I smelled a friend‚Äôs prenatal vitamins yesterday, and they actually smelled good, so I know it‚Äôs possible. I was excited about Perelel originally, but I could never recommend the brand if they continue smelling this bad. I‚Äôve had many non-pregnant friends smell them to assure me I‚Äôm not just hyper-sensitive. They‚Äôve all been shocked. It‚Äôs just so gross. 

Thanks, 

Caroline
tags: internal/log, complaint/smell-taste, WTR2-P, other/fishy, complaint-date/2024-10-21, #638632, refund/courtesy, refund/denied

body_text:
Hello Perelel¬†Customer¬†Service Team, 

Recently I just ordered my second trimester prenatal-vitamin¬†and after taking it felt very uncomfortable. I can smell very fishy from the vitamin and it makes me feel nauseous. I really wanna give it a try¬†but still don't feel good. I am wondering if I can return the rest of it?

body_text:
Hello, 

I have been ordering Perelel since my 2nd trimester of pregnancy. I continued ordering to "postpartum" Mom Multi-pack as a loyal customer; however, I realized that there's no magnesium capsules anymore here and there's a new capsule for "stress", so I was happy to take it. But as I ¬†read a little more on the label and it is from Ashwaghanda herbs. I believe it has been giving me vivid nightmares and palpitations. I think like other trimester boxes, where Perelel label it as "Omega 3" capsules, Magnesium, etc., the stress capsule should be labeled as "ashwaghanda" not Stress to not mislead customers or mommies. ¬†Hence, I skipped my Oct 27 order for November supply as this has a worse effect on me compared to my 2nd and 3rd trimester packs. 

I would like to return this order # 654031 for a refund or an exchange for 2nd trimester prenatal vitamins. I stop using it and still have 2 weeks worth of vitamin packets. How do I proceed with that request? 

Thank you for your support. Looking forward to hear from your customer support soon. 
V/R, 
- 
Christina Felix

subject: Order #657303
body_text:
Hi Perelel team, 
I hope you day is going well! It pains me greatly to have to write this email as I did so much research into different companies and the benefits of Perelel‚Äôs prenatals vs every other competitor were so much better and the nutrients and organization as a whole is¬†so much more aligned with my personal ideas of what I was to provide for my unborn child. The list goes on for why I chose Perelel as my prenatal choice. But I can‚Äôt. I simply can not stomach the smell of the pills. I have tried. I have tried leaving them out in the open for a while to air out. I have tried refrigerating them to avoid them creating a smell. I have tried taking them at different times of the day. I have tried using my liquid vitamins and spraying it on them to mask the smell of them but I can not. I gag. I have vomitted. I have tried. I really have. I just can not continue to put this much effort into this for my prenatals when I have so much else to focus on as well. I hope you understand and will allow me to return the remainder of my package. Thank you for reading my rant.

body_text:
Good morning. 

I'm trying to cancel my prescription¬†but im unable to access my account (email: skamara1@umbc.edu) (mailto:skamara1@umbc.edu) 

Thank you 

On Sat, Aug 31, 2024 at 1:46‚ÄØPM Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 

Hi Sama, 

Thank you for following up! Since our vitamins include things like iron, zinc & vitamin C (all essential nutrients we wouldn't want to leave out!), they can irritate your stomach lining especially early in the morning. In order to minimize any symptoms of nausea, we recommend taking your Perelel Pack on a full stomach or, even better, splitting up your pills and taking with your meals throughout the day, especially as your body adjusts to a new vitamin routine. Additionally, to minimize any lingering smells or aftertaste, you can also pop your Perelel Pack in the freezer prior to taking your vitamins. 

We also wanted to introduce you to our 1st Trimester Prenatal Vitamin Powder ‚Äî created for the days you just aren't up for taking your pack. Trust us, we've been there! This powder contains the essentials from your prenatal pack to cover your baseline needs in an easy, drinkable format that will help ease digestion and nausea. It just needs to be mixed with your cool liquid of choice and taken with a full stomach. This can be particularly helpful when your sense of smell is amplified in the 1st Trimester. (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-vitamin-powder) 

Thanks for updating your due date! This will ensure your subscription will automatically update alongside your due date so you receive the right pack for your trimester and into postpartum. 

Let us know any additional questions or if we can help swap out your subscription! 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Thu, Aug 29, 2024, at 09:50 PM, Sama Kamara < skamara26@gmail.com> wrote: (mailto:skamara26@gmail.com) 
Good evening 

I have confirmed that my due date is March 23rd 2025 

I just received my 2nd new package for the first trimester. It was a struggle finishing the first pack. 
Is there a different way of taking the pills. My stomach is unable to handle the 5 pills without even gagging. 

Thank you 

On Thu, Jul 25, 2024, at 07:28 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hi Sama, 

Thanks for sharing your tentative due date! This will ensure your subscription will automatically update alongside your due date so you receive the right pack for your trimester and into postpartum. 

As a heads up, your Perelel subscription follows the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG) defined trimesters: 
-1st Trimester: Week 0 through Week 13 
-2nd Trimester: Week 14 through Week 27 
-3rd Trimester: Week 28 through Week 40+ 

While the timing of when you start your vitamins with us doesn't always exactly align with your trimester, rest assured all of our packs will keep your needs covered during any overlap weeks! 

Want to connect with moms with a similar due date? Join our Geneva group now! (https://app.geneva.com/invite/997e7178-3982-4480-811f-252001048727) 

Feel free to let us know if you have any additional questions or see more FAQs here :) (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Thu, Jul 25, 2024, at 02:21 PM, Sama Kamara < skamara26@gmail.com> wrote: (mailto:skamara26@gmail.com) 
Thank you so much for the reply. 

I believe the due date will be March 23rd, 2025 . Will confirm with my OBGYN first week of August 

Thank you :) 

On Tue, Jul 16, 2024, at 01:58 AM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hi Sama, 

Congratulations!! We were able to locate your subscription account that you were referring to under: skamara1@umbc.edu (most recent order #528020 on 6/22). We have updated your subscription to the (mailto:skamara1@umbc.edu) 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack. We'd love to collect your due date here so your subscription will automatically update alongside your pregnancy without any changes needed on your side! (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack) Could you kindly share your current due date so we can add this to your account? 

So you don't go a day without pills, we recommend taking your Conception Support Pack until you receive your next order of the (https://perelelhealth.com/products/conception-support-pack) 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack. However, we do suggest to stop taking the CoQ10 supplement in the pack, which is the orange capsule (seen (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack) here). Although there is no reason to think that CoQ10 is unsafe during pregnancy, most women do not need to continue it once pregnant. Your (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/our-vitamin-packs) 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack is now set to ship on (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack) 07/22/2024. Please let us know if you would like us to process the order at an earlier date! 

We know the early days of pregnancy can be plagued by nausea which can of course be made worse by a new supplement routine. Remember to always take your vitamins on a full stomach and with a full glass of water! Some customers find taking before bed and even popping their pack in the freezer before taking can help eliminate any lingering smells or tastes - you can see more tips & tricks here! Also, our medical co-founder, Dr. Bayati, loves how our packs allow her particularly sick patients to cover their baseline needs on days when they cannot stomach the full pack (or anything at all!) by taking only the smaller white folate pill! We also recommend (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/your-complete-guide-to-taking-all-natural-supplements) this article, which highlights what foods to eat in the 1st Trimester and can be very helpful when navigating this journey! (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/food-to-eat-in-first-trimester-of-pregnancy) 

You can also check out our free Label Checker online to check your other ingestible + topical products to ensure they are pregnancy safe. Additionally, we wanted to invite you to our (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/unclean15) Geneva group to connect with other women who are in the same trimester as you to ask any and all questions! (https://app.geneva.com/invite/997e7178-3982-4480-811f-252001048727) 

Best, 
Team Perelel

Thank you for your patience!

subject: White Spots on Core Prenatal Vitamins
body_text:
Hello, 

I am concerned about white spots that I see on the core prenatal vitamins in a majority of my packs the past month. I have noticed this before in some of the packs previous months and thrown them away, but this I have noticed this in at least 15 of my packs this month. Besides feared health concerns, I am wasting money. Are the white spots that I am seeing normal/can they be explained? 

Warm Regards, 
Kayla M. Dietrich

subject: Request to Cancel Subscription and Refund for Prenatal Vitamins
body_text:
Dear Perelel Team, 
I recently purchased two boxes of your prenatal vitamins and, unfortunately, have encountered an issue that makes it impossible for me to continue using them. The first box had such a strong, unpleasant smell that I initially thought it was spoiled, which led me to purchase a second box just a few days later. However, upon opening the second box, I realized it had the same rancid smell as the first. 
The odor is so overpowering that it causes me to gag and vomit, and despite my efforts, including trying to store the packets in the freezer, I have only been able to take a few of them. I cannot continue using the prenatal vitamins because of this issue. 
Given the situation, I would like to request a cancellation of my subscription and a refund for both boxes, as I am unable to use the product. 
Please let me know the next steps to process this request. Thank you for your understanding and assistance. 
Best regards, 
Mikaila

subject: Refund Request
body_text:
I purchased a subscription for the second trimester pack and received it today. I‚Äôm suffering from really extreme nausea with my pregnancy and smell/taste sensitivity. It‚Äôs hard for me take any pills. I was really excited about your product but after trying it, there is just no way I can use them. The smell, taste, and after-taste of the pills is so insanely strong, I couldn‚Äôt take one, let alone manage to force four down. The product says ‚Äúno-nausea‚Äù formula and I‚Äôm sorry but that is just not accurate. It‚Äôs obviously a program for pregnant women, who are often already nauseous or queasy so I really think the brand should try to re-formulate to make them better so people can actually use them. I would like to return and be fully refunded. And also, please cancel my subscription as well. I‚Äôm sure the product quality is amazing, but the formula, packaging and other aspects prevent it from being realistically used. 

Thank you,
Marina

subject: Request for Return and Refund of Prenatal Vitamins
body_text:
Hello,

I‚Äôm reaching out regarding my recent first-trimester order of your prenatal vitamins. After thorough research, I was excited to try them, but unfortunately, they didn‚Äôt work for me as I‚Äôd hoped.

The strong smell of the vitamins makes them very difficult for me to take, (makes me want to vomit) and the requirement of five pills per day has become overwhelming. As a result, I find myself avoiding them, which defeats their purpose.

I‚Äôve only used two sachets, so there are still 28 unused. I understand that the box is open, but I‚Äôd like to inquire if a return and refund would be possible under these circumstances.

Thank you for any assistance you can offer, and I appreciate your understanding.

Best regards,
Cristina

subject: order #680594
body_text:
Hello! 

I have been trying to conceive for a while now and got so many instagram ads for this product I thought it might be worth giving it a try. I received my order just before going away for several days for work and was excited about the individual packs for easy travel! However, I did not realize there were 5 total pills I would be having to take :( The scent/smell of them is rather strong and I also didn't realize I had to take on a full stomach. I've only used about 3-4 packs (the duration of my work trip). Is there any possible way to send the remaining back and be refunded? 

Any help is so appreciated. Thank you so much! 

Melissa

subject: Question about Mom Multi Support
body_text:
Hello, 
I just recently purchased Mom Multi Support for the first time. I have taken 2 packs so far. 
Are all of the pills intended to be taken at once? I have been taking them all together after dinner, but I have noticed that my tummy doesn't feel so well afterward. I was wondering if it would be helpful to break them up; take some in the morning and some in the evening. Do you have any suggestions as to which ones would be better in the AM vs PM? 
Thanks so much, 
Alisha 
--

subject: Re: A shipment from order #683272 has been delivered
body_text:
Hey there! 

I‚Äôve been talking my supplements for a week and experiencing extreme gastrointestinal issues. Cramping, nausea, very loose stool. The cramp are truly unbearable. Has this ever been reported and is there an idea of what supplement it could be causing it?! I started with just the conception pack and was doubled over with pain and had to take a prescription stomach cramping medication to have to stop. I then introduced one pill at a time from my order without the pack, first iron, then fertility+, then hormonal balance. All came with cramping that i was not able to functionally highly during my work week. I gave the pack one more attempt and again, very very very cramping followed by gastro issues. All of the supplements i have taken before from one her companies but due to all the research and information transparency i thought your company would be the best!! The work you are doing is fantastic but sadly my stomach may be too sensitive. 

If you have any idea on the cause, i would love to know to see if eliminating would be best but if you‚Äôre unable to help identify I am requesting a return to be started on these supplements for the time being. 

Thank you.

Nicole Keefe

Kathryn

subject: 1st trimester drink vitamin mix
body_text:
Hi there, 

I recently purchased the 1st trimester drink mix and just wanted to give my review. 

While I am sure that the vitamins are of good quality, I cannot seem to keep the drink mix down long enough for it to work. By the time I am finished with the drink mix it usually always makes my stomach so upset I vomit them up. 

I usually try to get half down and then immediately fall¬†asleep to keep them down. It's challenging however because I need to brush my teeth before bed and between drinking the vitamins and brushing my teeth I nearly always vomit the vitamins and my bedtime snack up. 

I am getting so frustrated. I am just going to have to buy another prenatal vitamin from the drug store. I am sad about that because I really like perelel as a company. I should have just gotten the pill vitamins but didn't see them as an option until after I order the drink mix. I only have about 4 weeks left in my first trimester so it's not worth it financially or timeline wise to reorder the pill version of your vitamins. 

Just wanted to share my experience. 

-Holly
tags: complaint-date/2024-10-29, WPT1-B, internal/log, complaint/nausea, handled-by-siena

subject: Nausea with Prenatal
body_text:
Hello, 

I have experienced incredible nausea with my 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack from Perelel. If I do not take the prenatal pack, I do not experience nausea. Because of this, I would like a refund as I am within the 30 day period. Thank you for your help. 

Best, 
Rachel Dody

subject: Conception pack
body_text:
Hello,
My name is Kiran Shah and I ordered the conception pack because of all the amazing things I hear about Perelel. I have taken it twice already with a meal and full glass of water and I cannot handle the smell. I have a very sensitive stomach and don‚Äôt think I will be able to continue taking them. I‚Äôm so sorry and truly apologize for this. Can you please provide me with some guidance on how I can return them to get a refund? Thank you! 

My order number is 690485.

Thank you for your understanding. 
Best Regards,
Kiran Shah

subject: 1st Trimester Powder Pack Issue
body_text:
Hi there, 

I recently ordered the 1st Trimester powder packs after using the 1st Trimester pill packs for a month. I originally switched because the smell of the pills was very potent to my pregnancy nose! However, every time I use the powder packs I end up throwing up, regardless of time of day or if I've taken it with food. I'm wondering if I am able to get the 1st Trimester pill packs as a replacement for the powder without having to pay for another pack because I won't be able to use those anymore. 

For reference, my most recent order number is #680741. 

Please let me know if that's possible. 
Thanks! 
Allison

body_text:
Hello, 

I recently purchased the First Trimester pack and I was super excited to try these vitamins solely based on the high quality ingredients involved. I tried to put the vitamins in the freezer to help with the taste but it unfortunately did not help. I wish so badly I could ignore the taste of these vitamins but the smell and taste makes me more nauseous than anything. Unfortunately I am requesting a refund for these vitamins if possible as I can't convince myself to consume them anymore. I love what your company is doing and am sadden by the taste of the vitamins. Thank you so much for your help! 

All the best, 
Ashley Fermo

subject: Refund for order #686081
body_text:
Good morning, 

I recently made a purchase (order #686081) for my wife to try the trimester prenatals. She threw up one night and has felt uneasy the past couple of nights after taking the prenatals. She is not sure she can take them anymore based on how she feels after taking them. Could I please get a refund for the prenatal pack? I was hoping to possibly get a refund on the greens as well. She doesn't like the flavor and probably won't drink anymore of it. Thank you and have a great rest of the¬†day! 

Respectfully, 
Zach Boyette 

Sent from my iPhone

subject: order #697425 and #653638
body_text:
Hi! 
In regards to my 2 most recent orders #697425 and #653638, I wanted to return the pre/pro biotics from both orders. I really do not like how they taste, and they are becoming more and more aversive as my pregnancy progresses. I would also
 like to cancel both subscriptions for the powders (pre/pro biotic and the electrolytes). I like the electrolytes, but I have way too much right now. 
I could not find an easy way to delay/cancel these subscriptions like I‚Äôve been able to do with other companies. Can you please help with these returns and cancelations? I am happy to send back the two pre/pro biotics, I have not opened
 them. 
Please get back to me when you can! 
Thank you, 
Shanna Bahry

subject: Subscription
body_text:
Hi, 
I just cancelled my subscription after I was notified that my next shipment would be sent out soon.¬† I didn't realize I chose a subscription.¬† Unfortunately, I've barely been able to take these vitamins- I've had maybe 3 packs and was unable to continue because¬†of the smell and taste. Even after throwing them in the freezer, I'm having a hard time with them. 

It would be great if you could make sure that I'm not billed for my November shipment and that it does not actually get shipped to me as I will not be able to use them. 

Thank you 

Veronica Carlson

subject: Headaches with Hormonal Balance Support
body_text:
Hello, 

My name is Lea Rossignol and I recently purchased a subscription to the hormone balance support vitamins. Unfortunately, I tried to take them for three days straight and have had horrible headaches. I tried to stop and then start again to see if the headache were in fact from the pills and sure enough they are. I already cancelled my subscription but is there any way to get my money back for this bottle and return it? I am also curious if you have had this feedback before. Am I the only one? 

Thanks, 
Lea Rossignol

subject: Return
body_text:

subject: Request for refund and return due to unknown allergic reaction.
body_text:
Dear Perele team, 

I heard highly about your products so I wanted to try and ultimately switch my prenatal vitamin to one of yours. I recently purchased the 2nd Trimester Prenatal Pack from your website but unfortunately, I experienced a severe allergic reaction and vomited right after taking it.üò≠ 

Due to this issue, I kindly request a refund and would like to return the product. Please let me know the next steps in the return process. 

Thank you for your understanding and support. 

 ID: NIKLBNR4 

Best reguarrds, 
Grace

subject: Prenatal refund
body_text:
Hello, 

Unfortunately I would like to request a refund of my last perelel order. I wanted to love these vitamins but they are making me nauseous. I've tried pairing it with food, taking a d different times of the day and other things but more often then not I feel sick right after. I also am not enjoying the taste of the powdered greens.

Order # 692958


Thank you!

Thank you 

Katie Herman

subject: Refund 1st vitamin pack
body_text:
Hi, 

I am emailing because I would like a refund on my first purchase. I specifically¬†bought the 1st trimester in hopes of calming down my nausea, but 2 days of taking the 1st trimester pack made my nausea x10 worse & I was vomiting¬†twice a day. As soon as I stopped taking them, my nausea calmed down. 

I really wanted to love them, but my body/stomach does not agree¬†with them. How can I return the remaining vitamins & receive a refund? I have an account with this email address, and just cancelled the subscription. 

Thank you so much for your time & help. I look forward to hearing from¬†you. 
-- 
Laura Arreola 
University of California, Berkeley 
B.A., Development Studies, Class of 2016 
(925) 848-6394

subject: Missing pills from packets
body_text:
Hello, 

I have had a subscription with your company for the preconception vitamins for the last 5 months. I was on vacation recently and packed my vitamins. One day I was going to take them and noticed there was only 3 vitamins instead of 5. Luckily, I brought an extra packet just in case so I didn‚Äôt miss a day. I‚Äôve had two more packets from this same shipment that were also missing 2 vitamins inside each of them. It was very inconvenient and upsetting to have multiple packets missing vitamins, especially after paying $50.00 a month for this subscription. This subscription isn‚Äôt inexpensive, and I would like to receive some sort of reimbursement for my missing vitamins and the inconvenience of wasted packets of vitamins. I‚Äôm very supportive of your company and I have been recommending your company and product to friends, family and coworkers. I look forward to hearing from you soon, and have a good day.

Thank you,
Emily Bay
tags: internal/log, siena-follow-needed, assisted-by-siena, complaint/quality, complaint-date/2024-11-04, #700263, WCON-P

subject: Cancel subscription
body_text:
Hi there 

Can you please help cancel my subscription? Due to the smell and taste of the pills I wasn‚Äôt able to open the second box I got delivered. These aren‚Äôt nausea-friendly pills unfortunately so I had to switch brands - these were quite hard for me to take and the times I tried I kept burping them up and didn‚Äôt feel great (tmi but sharing my feedback incase it‚Äôs helpful!) 

Thank you, 
Chelsea

On Aug 27, 2024, at 1:49‚ÄØAM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hi Chelsea, 

Thanks for sharing your due date! This will ensure your subscription will automatically update alongside your due date so you receive the right pack for your trimester and into postpartum. 

As a heads up, your Perelel subscription follows the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists (ACOG) defined trimesters: 
-1st Trimester: Week 0 through Week 13 
-2nd Trimester: Week 14 through Week 27 
-3rd Trimester: Week 28 through Week 40+ 

While the timing of when you start your vitamins with us doesn't always exactly align with your trimester, rest assured all of our packs will keep your needs covered during any overlap weeks! 

Want to connect with moms with a similar due date? Join our Geneva group now! (https://app.geneva.com/invite/997e7178-3982-4480-811f-252001048727) 

Feel free to let us know if you have any additional questions or see more FAQs here :) (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Best, 
Team Perelel

subject: Subscription problems
body_text:
Hello, 
I just wanted¬† to let you know the true reason¬† why I canceled my subscription, as when you are in the process of canceling none of the selections were correct. 
Upon setting up my subscription it said it would¬† switch over vitamins¬† with each trimester¬† so I would not have to go and edit it every time...it does not. It just renewed¬† my 1st trimester pills...I caught¬† it in time and edited¬† it, but the
 dates are way off and was going¬† to send¬† my pills way late...it doesn't calculate¬† when the trimesters actually switch, so you just end up having¬† to go on and edit it anyway.¬† It's a big pain, just another thing to remember.¬† So if it doesn't¬† do what it
 says it does, then it's¬† just jot worth it ( and I did put in the correct¬† due date so it should¬† be able to calculate¬† trimester dates). And the pills made my stomach feel not the best if taken on an empty¬† stomach or a light snack...which isn't¬† that bad
 but just another¬† thing.. 
So if you have¬† a way of fixing¬† this¬† I might return. Just thought¬† you should¬† know. It's¬† not as convenient as advertised. 
I'd rather just grab my vitamins at the grocery¬† store . 
 
Sent from Samsung Galaxy smartphone.

subject: Order Error
body_text:
Hi there, 

Last month, I received my order from Perelel, which I thought was the 1st Trimester Prenatal Pack. However, I accidentally opted for the powder pre-natal¬†instead of the capsules. I was going to just deal with it but the powder doesn't blend into water very well plus I am not a fan of the taste. (https://perelelhealth.com/products/1st-trimester-prenatal-pack?view=trimester) 

My family and I left the day after receiving this order for a 2-week trip to Maine so I completely forgot, when we got back, to notify you of this issue and request a refund. 

Yesterday, I was reminded of this when I received another shipment of the first trimester powder packs. So, there were actually two errors on my part with this order -- and that is that I accidentally ordered it as a subscription, which was not my intention. 

Is there any remedy for this? I think I cancelled the subscription accurately but is there any way I could receive a refund for the orders that I received¬†that weren't the product that I initially wanted? 

Please see my order numbers in the attachment below! Thank you so much for your time! 
-- 
Haley Shepherd CEO + Creative Director AlysonHaley.com (http://alysonhaley.com/)

subject: Product Issue - Order 708849
body_text:
Good afternoon team, 

I wanted to reach out with unfortunately bad news. I was incredibly excited to try the products as I‚Äôve read great reviews, fantastic ingredients and what your company stands for as I try to prepare for pregnancy hopefully after pregnancy loss. 

Unfortunately, the smell after taking for two days is unbearable. I‚Äôve tried everything I can to mitigate it, but nothing has, or can help. Even after two days, I can no longer take them due throwing up from the smell today. 

I am incredibly sorry but wanted to reach out as I no longer can take the remaining 28 packs already due to this issue and worry that I have wasted money during this important journey. 

Thank you for your time. 

Best, 
Sarah

Hi, 

I just received order 710147 and the order was just delivered but multiple items in my order are damaged. 

I was home when they delivered it but nobody came to the front door, it was just left on the stairs leading up to my house. 

My conception support pack is completely smashed and some of the bags are damaged. 

The cap of the daily probiotic wasn‚Äôt screwed on properly and the inner seal is ripped. The priobiotic bottle also didn‚Äôt have the plastic seal on the outside as my fertility support. 

And my symbiotic greens canister had a hole so there‚Äôs powder that shakes out. 

I‚Äôve attached photos for your reference. 

I‚Äôm a new customer, this is my second order and how everything came damaged seems unacceptable. 

Is there any way a replacement order can be rushed? 

Thanks, 
Chia-Ling Dean

subject: Subscription
body_text:
Hello, 
I am trying to log in and cancel my subscription for next months prenatal vitamins. I started with my first trimester pack and can't even take them. My nauseous is so bad with the smell of these vitamins that I just end up throwing up. I have tried eating them with multiple foods to mask the smell and I still can't keep them down. 
How can¬†I cancel my subscription? Or is this something you can do on your end? I just don't want to end up paying so much for something I can't¬†afford¬†right now or even keep down. Thanks in advance for your help. I look forward¬†to hearing from you. 

Crissel Seia 
847-361-2172

subject: Prenatal question
body_text:
Hey there! 
I hope this¬†email finds you well, 
I recently got my second box of first trimester but for some reason I think my body is not digesting well the vitamins, i am still on box one because there are days that I cant take the vitamins because of my nausea. After I take the vitamins my body just feels weird, and I get more nauseous. 

Is there anything do you guys think I am doing wrong? I eat before I take them, and I drink plenty of water with them and throughout the day. My mom thinks I should try different vitamins but I am sad I just got my second box and I also like the vitamins you offer. I am just not sure if maybe they are not for me? 

I would love some advice if you have any! 
Thank you so much; 
Nathaly P

subject: Sleep support tampered with?
body_text:
Hi, I ordered sleep support and the synbiotic greens powder. When I opened the package today, the sleep support was not sealed and was leaking powder into the package. Can I please have a refund or a replacement as I have no intention of using one that arrived open. Thank you. 




-Anni Kanellopoulos

subject: Order#703994
body_text:
Hello! I received my shipment by subscription and started taking it. Today I open a daily vitamins pack and this is how the pill looked like( see photo attached). 
It comes as 5 daily prenatal vitamins in a pack, unfortunately I took 4 pills without taking a close look and then stopped after seeing the last pill. It had brown spots and a hair stick to it. I don‚Äôt even want to think how the 4 that i actually took looked like 
. I‚Äôm on my third trimester, and it‚Äôs absolutely unacceptable to receive vitamins like this. It could be mold, it could be anything that can potentially harm my unborn child. 
Please advise. 
Best Regards, 
Valeria Ford

subject: Re: A shipment from order #711607 is on the way
body_text:
Hi, 

I apologize but I did not see that the cellular hydration was also being shipped to me. I have had difficulties with this product being completely removed from being sent to me. This would be the third time I unfortunately have had to reach out in regards to this product being shipped to me as it is not part of my subscription at the moment. My stomach is just not being able to handle it during these beginning stages of pregnancy. I put an order in for the months worth of the 1st trimester pack, but somehow even though my account doesn‚Äôt show it, the cellular hydration keeps being added on. 
Is there a way to make sure this does not keep happening in the future? I just am not budgeting for that charge to be added on and want to make sure it doesn‚Äôt surprise me again. 

Thank you for your help. 

Best, 

Berit Harris

subject: Perelel Subscription
body_text:
Good Morning, 

My name is Brittany and I recently purchased a subscription for the 1st trimester (ID: 10DZEK5N). 

With all of my pregnancies, I get really sick, so I was very excited when I found Perelel this pregnancy after doing a lot of research and reading so many positive reviews. However I‚Äôve tried two days in a row to take a single pill of the four pill packet and my body simply cannot handle the taste/smell without immediately vomiting. I‚Äôve tried everything and cannot keep these down, which I am very disappointed and upset about because I truly feel these are the best prenatals for women and the health of their growing baby.¬† Normally I would never ask but under these circumstances, I am kindly asking for a refund and would be happy to still leave a good review of the company as I still support and respect your mission. Thank you for your time and I look forward to hearing from you. 

Kindly, 
Brittany Gribbins

Have other women received packs w tears before? 

Thanks,
Jess Makram

subject: Conception pack return
body_text:
Good evening,

I recently got off of birth control and started taking the conception pack you guys offer, as well as the hormone support supplement. 
I have been extremely nauseous and taking my conception pack today, I instantly vomited the supplements back up. The smell and taste was so off putting that it actually made my nausea worse. The smell is in my hands and it won‚Äôt come off no matter how much I wash them and I have been burping up the taste of them all day. I don‚Äôt have any complaints about the hormone balance. 

Am I able to return the conception pack? 
Thank you,
Emily

Hi I have recently started the prenatal vitamins as conception pack. Conclusions - the vitamin packs from your brand really don‚Äôt work for me! subject: Inquiry About First Trimester Pack and Medication Interaction
body_text:
Dear Perelel Team, 
I hope this message finds you well. I recently purchased your First Trimester Pack, which includes the Prenatal Core, Anti-Nausea Blend, Core Prenatal Omega DHA + EPA, Folate, and Anti-Nausea Blend. 
Currently, I am experiencing constant nausea and frequent vomiting. My OB-GYN has prescribed Tums after meals and Diclegis (doxylamine + pyridoxine) every 12 hours to manage these symptoms. 
Before I start taking the vitamins, I wanted to clarify if the Anti-Nausea Blend in your First Trimester Pack contains any ingredients that might duplicate or interfere with the medications I‚Äôm already taking. Should I consider omitting any of the supplements in this case? 
I appreciate your guidance and look forward to hearing from you. 

Gabriela

subject: Subscriber - Nausea
body_text:
Hi Perelel team - 

I‚Äôm a loyal subscriber and had taken the conception support packs, then followed by the first trimester packs for several months, and I‚Äôm now 10 weeks pregnant and going through a tough 1st trimester where I‚Äôm very nauseous. 

I usually take the prenatals after dinner, before bed, and the past two nights I‚Äôve gotten so sick after taking them that I have thrown them up. Do you have any suggestions? 

I don‚Äôt want to switch brands as I really believe in your methodology! I just want to make sure I‚Äôm getting some nutrients vs throwing them up. 

Thanks! 
Sarah¬†-- 

_________________________

subject: Strange taste and smell
body_text:
Hi there! 

I‚Äôve been taking your supplements from the beginning of my of my fertility journey through pregnancy, and now currently almost one year postpartum. I‚Äôve never had an issue. However, the last shipment I got had a really off putting taste and smell from the packets. I could barely keep them open next to me let alone swallow them. Is there a way to get a refund or a replacement for the month? I‚Äôm definitely not pregnant so it‚Äôs not that lol. 

Thanks so much,
Ena Sundquist
tags: internal/log, WMOM-P, #702701, complaint-date/2024-11-12, complaint/nausea, complaint/smell-taste, complaint-smell

subject: Subscription Delivery in Hot Climates
body_text:
Hello, 

I just subscribed to receive monthly shipments of prenatal vitamins and I'm curious how hot climates will affect the supplements come next summer. I live in Las Vegas, so temperatures often reach 115¬∞ during the day in late July/August and stay above 90¬∞ for about two months straight. With most carriers not having air-conditioned cargo, my packages are typically exposed to high temps for at least a day before arriving to my house. I'm curious how these temperatures would affect the product and if the efficacy of the vitamins would be compromised? If high temperatures would be expected to negatively affect the product, would it be possible to have multiple months shipped out at once in the spring to avoid summer shipments? 

Thanks, 
- Marissa Dowalter-Miracle
tags: general-product/safety, siena-follow-needed, complaint/heat, assisted-by-siena, other/subscription-OTP

Thank you. Please let me know if you need any additional information.

subject: Vitamin return
body_text:
Hello, 

My name is Blair Pomeroy and I ordered some vitamins from you in my first and second trimester. I tried the pill form but unfortunately they made me too sick so I tried the powder form and that too made me feel nauseous. Had severe nausea during this pregnancy and my account was set up on auto fill and it sent me a box of the powder that I never opened because it made me feel sick to my stomach. I was hoping to be able to return it. 

I also ordered a box of unopened pill form vitamins for my 2nd trimester because I had tried them again later in this pregnancy hoping I was over my aversion and they still made me feel icky as well. So I was hoping for to return the unopened pack of those vitamins as well that were also on auto fill at the time. Both boxes literally haven‚Äôt even been taken out of the box they were shipped in. So you should be able to resell them. 

Thank you so much 

Blair Pomeroy 
Sent from my iPhone

I started a subscription for the first trimester prenatal pills - I was able to get halfway through the first box but the taste and smell of the pills is not very pleasant, and I have not been able to take these since without throwing up. The second month order was placed through before I was able to cancel, and therefore I will be wasting a whole
Box - order 704174. I was looking for a refund. I wanted to love these but I just can‚Äôt take them. 

Thank you, 
Lauren Furfari

subject: 2nd trimester pack
body_text:
Hello there! 

I just ordered my first 2nd trimester pack with you and started taking this on Sunday. 
I was also using the first trimester pack that my friend had left over and shared with me. 

I take my packet at night, right after dinner. Between my 2nd trimester pack arriving and completing my first one I had about 10 days where I was using a generic prenatal. Now that I‚Äôm back to taking perelel packs I notice that my sickness and intolerance to food during the day has increased significantly and I‚Äôm wondering if it‚Äôs possibly related to the prenatal pack and if you‚Äôve had
Any other women experience this?

-should I try taking these at a different time? 
- does continuing the prenatal packs outweigh my side effects and decreased appetite / nausea 
(I have pollen food allergy syndrome and miss out on a lot of fresh foods/proteins because of this) 
- is it worthwhile to try some anti nausea meds? I‚Äôm trying to avoid taking anything extra that I don‚Äôt absolutely need. I have also heard B6 could help. 

Thank you for your help! 

Bethany 
Sent from my iPhone

Thank you for your time and support!
Jessica Rau

subject: Refund for ORDER NO. #720008
body_text:
Good Evening,

I would like to request a refund for my recent order of the Third Trimester Prenatal packs as these are not working for me. Since starting the prenatal packs, I have had terrible nausea and upset stomach. I have tried putting them in the fridge (to help with the smell) and taking them right before bed as suggested by your website, but neither has helped. I have not had issues with other prenatal vitamins so not sure what the issue is. 


Many thanks,
Maja Krsmanovic 

Sent from my iPhone

subject: Re: A shipment from order #725584 is on the way
body_text:
Hi Perelel, 

I want to know if I can get a refund for my items. The conception pack has the fish oil pill with the rest of the pills, so they all smell fishy and I‚Äôm worried about cross contamination. I took one of the prenatals and had diarrhea afterwards. 

Does the Sleep support have Honey? I cannot take products with honey. 

For the Cellular hydration powder, I have an allergy to Mango. 

Finally, for the Synbiotic greens, I am unsure if I will have a reaction to the Bilberry Extract. I am unfamiliar with what that is, and I am concerned, as I have a lot of allergies. 

I cannot use any of these items :( 

Thank you, 

Kyla 

Sent from my iPhone 
On Nov 15, 2024, at 11:37‚ÄØAM, Perelel Support <hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: 

Hi Kyla, 

Thank you for reaching out! Though there are no shellfish within the pack, our Omega gelcap is made from fish oil. If you have a shellfish allergy, we recommend that you avoid that vitamin. However, many of our routine builders here do not include this omega. (https://perelelhealth.com/collections/routine-builders) 

We generally don‚Äôt recommend opening our capsules, but if you do have issues, however, you can open them and mix them into a drink. We would recommend a smoothie or yogurt to help with any taste and absorption issues (see a great smoothie recipe here!). (https://perelelhealth.com/blogs/news/recipe-strawberry-green-be-well-smoothie?_pos=2&_sid=58139cb6f&_ss=r) 

We apologize for any inconvenience and please let us know if you have any additional questions! 

Best, 
Team Perelel 

On Fri, Nov 15, 2024, at 01:44 PM, Perelel Support < hi@perelelhealth.com> wrote: (mailto:hi@perelelhealth.com) 
Hello Kyla, 

Thank you for reaching out to Perelel! We have received your email and our customer support team will be reaching out to assist you shortly. Our business hours are Monday through Friday from 9 am to 5 pm PST. Please allow 1 to 2 business days for someone from our team to get back to you. We'll do our best to reply to your email as quickly as possible. 

In the meantime, be sure to check out our FAQ page for help with general inquiries, managing your subscription, shipping and returns. (https://perelelhealth.com/pages/faq) 

Thank you for your patience! 

On Fri, Nov 15, 2024, at 01:44 PM, Kyla Thorpe < katgold2008@bellsouth.net> wrote: (mailto:katgold2008@bellsouth.net) 
Hello! 

I have 2 questions for you: 

1. I have extreme pill anxiety and have difficultly swallowing capsules. For the prenatal, for example, can I open the capsule up and mix it in a food or liquid to take it? I keep trying to take pills and end up spitting them out and wasting them. 

2. The other question I have is about the omega pill that has anchovies or sardines. Do you know of any issues with people with shellfish allergies? I have heard that anchovies, for some reason, can sometimes cause reactions or people with shellfish allergies. 

Thank you, 

Kyla

subject: Very high Folate in conception pack
body_text:
Hi, I just started your conception support pack because I am planning a pregnancy soon. The pills are very smelly and cause stomach problems for me. I did a quick research and found out that the daily maximum recommended folate is 1000 mcg and your daily packs contain more than 1500 mcg. I bought the product thinking it was formulated by experts and did not do my own research beforehand. I wonder why they contain this much folate and is there research backing up this amount? Please let me know,

Seda Kuruoglu

subject: 2nd trimester package
body_text:
Hello 

I got the second trimester package this week, this is my third box. I noticed that the packaging has changed and when I opened the vitamins they had a change in smell. Were there changes made to the formula? I didn‚Äôt receive any notification stating there would be changes? Im a little concerned to be taking the vitamins when they look and smell so different.

subject: Refund Order #719724
body_text:
Hello, 
My name is Desiree Vemireddy and I am asking for a full refund for the first trimester pack. I threw up after taking the pills multiple¬†times. I even tried the trick of putting it in the freezer 30min-1hr before taking and tried taking it at night. The smell is absolutely horrendous. And the taste and smell for the powders are also not pleasing making me gag trying to take it down. including add it in a smoothie vs water itself. I've tried other off the counter products and am able to take those down fine. I was so excited for Perelel,¬†I wanted to take it so badly but I could not take the taste and smell. My order number is #719724. I had ordered the cellular hydration powder, sleep support, 1st trimester prenatal pack, and synbiotics green powder and spent a total of $155.90 USD. Please let me know when this refund could be processed. Thank you!

subject: Product Question
body_text:
Product Question
-------------------------------
I have been taking the prenatals for a few months now and have had no issues with the products or being able to swallow them. I have taken the Egg Freeze, Conception Support, and 1st Trimester packs all with no problems. I've been taking the 2nd Trimester pack for about 2 weeks now and cannot take these vitamins without gagging. Last night I actually threw them up into my water glass and proceeded to throw up everything in my system in the toilet. I didn't think the prenatal pill itself changed from pack to pack but for some reason these prenatal pills are not going down the same way the others had. Can someone assist and explain if this is normal? Could it be the pack I received? I tried putting them in the fridge before but it doesn't help.
tags: internal/log, complaint/smell-taste, complaint/nausea, WTR2-P, complaint-date/2024-11-22, #700603, urgent

Joy Nestel

body_text:
Hello,

I recently started taking your hormone balance support and had a question regarding a rise in core body temperature. I use natural cycles to track my ovulation and cycle. I noticed that the next morning after I started taking the Hormone Balance Support when tracking my temperature first thing in the morning per my usual routine it was significantly higher. I don‚Äôt know if this is a coincidence, but I did think it was interesting since before taking it my rise in temperature wasn‚Äôt predicted for another 2 weeks. Wondering if anyone else has had this question or noticed this trend. 

Thank you! 
Molly Wall

body_text:

subject: 1st Trimester Prenatals
body_text:
Good evening! 

I am currently taking the 1st trimester prenatals ran into an issue of swallowing the pills yesterday and today. The soft gel one is no problem, but I just can't make myself swallow the capsules. 
Because of this, I have been opening the capsules and eating the contents one by one with spoonfuls of yogurt and applesauce (and what a wonderful taste combination that is. I do NOT recommend, but it does the job! hahaha). 

I know the ginger is meant to be timed release to help with nausea, but the only thing I have noticed is that it does seem to give me some heartburn. Are there any issues with me doing this? 
Kindest Regards, 
Kyla Stephens

subject: Returns
body_text:
Hi, I have been taking the perelel first trimester pack for about a month. Recently, I haven‚Äôt been able to take the pills and keep them down. This was after my second package had already shipped to me. I have the second package and have not opened it. I am inquiring if I can send them back for a refund. I would love to be able to take these vitamins, but unfortunately with nausea and morning sickness I don‚Äôt know that a pill version is going to be the best option for me right now. I have already canceled my subscription. Seeking advice on if I can send back the unopened package and receive a refund. 

Thank you for your time. 
- Cameron J

subject: Weird smell from Second Tri
body_text:
Hello - I am currently taking the second trimester prenatals and they have a very pungent, very strong smell to them. Much more pronounced than the first trimester and borderline intolerable. I now dread taking them. Is this how the second trimester formula is supposed to be? I know you change them up based on pregnancy progress but I just wanted to double check. It‚Äôs almost like they have gone bad but the expiration date is fine still. (Note - I had an entire box leftover from my first pregnancy that ended at 22.5 weeks, from July 2023). I don‚Äôt recall second tri smelling like this last time. The expiration date says 01/2025 so I started taking them again with this pregnancy as they were still well within that time frame.

Please advise. Thank you!


Amy Abt, Curator
Ma Jolie Society
MaJolieSociety.com
Life and style of the sophisticated femme

body_text:
Hi, I am writing to you about my last order# 738278 for my subscription service. I received the actual shipping envelope but there were no Fertility+ Support supplements inside the package. As you can see from the attached photos the envelope was damaged and taped and when I opened the package there was nothing inside (USPS tracking number 9400 1361 0577 4274 7775 91). 
Would you be able to re-ship this item to me with expedited shipping as I am now out of the product and should be taking them on a daily basis? My contact information is below. Thank you so much for your attention to this matter. 
Best regards, 
Alyssa Swanson 11 Leavenworth Road Apt. 104 Shelton, CT 06484

subject: Request for Refund - #695155
body_text:
Hello, 

I'm reaching out about order #695155. 

My husband has been liking the Men's Multi Support Pack, but I have had trouble taking the Conception Support Pack... the scent makes me gag and if/when I am able to swallow them, they give me strange-tasting burps. 

I'm wondering if you'd be willing to refund me for the latter? 

Thanks, 
Charlotte
tags: internal/log, complaint/smell-taste, email, complaint-date/2024-11-28, WCON-P

subject: Help with an order
body_text:
Hello, 

I‚Äôm so sorry to ask this but I was wondering what your return/refund policy is? I recently bought the prenatal first trimester and powdered green mix and while i love the concept of this company and the founders story, unfortunately the prenatals are still quite strong smelling and tasting and i wasnt able to get them down without wretching Ive just got such bad morning sickness and these are like most prenatals ive tried unfortunately i cant keep them down. 

I hate to ask but could I send them back and get a refund for the prenatal portion of my order? Like i said, the greens powder is great and I love it so far, just cant manage the prenatals. 

Thanks so much for any help with this i do love the company and support its drive to help women! 

Natalie Summers

subject: Fwd: A shipment from order #740857 has been delivered
body_text:
Aloha, 
Got my order yesterday and had the 1st packet of supplement this morning. 
One of the capsules smell soo terrible, idk if i should describe it as earthy or fishy. I dont have morning sickness or nausea at all, but soon as the packet opened, I gagged. 
I was able to swallow the other capsules just fine, but the smelly one.. as I put it close to my nose, everything got ejected out, and i been feeling sick the past 2hrs. 
Is it possible to return the rest of the supplement (29left) and get a refund? And i need to cxl the subscription. 
I dont have the courage to try another packet. 
Winnie

subject: Order #735983
body_text:
Hello, I am a first time buyer and recently placed an order for a 1st trimester pack (Order #735983)- excited and in love with the concept of this vitamin pack. However, after taking it for only day, the smell of the vitamins made me sick and made my nausea worse. I ended up burping up the vitamins all day long and could not stand the taste in my mouth. As much as I want to love these, I think the product and quality is not for me. 
Given these circumstances, I kindly request a refund for my purchase. Please let me know if you need any additional details or steps from my end to process this request. 
Thank you for your understanding, and I appreciate your prompt assistance. 
Kindly, 
Kayla Simon 
Sent from my iPhone

body_text:
Hi there,
I ordered two types of 1st trimester packs (pill pack and powder form). subject: Re: A shipment from order #726099 has been delivered
body_text:
Hello & Happy Saturday, 

I wanted to reach out and inquire about an issue that I have been having for quite a few months now in regards to your daily probiotic. I have been ordering since the month of July 2024. I started having symptoms of what seemed like constant fatigue, sneezing, migraines, itchy eyes, constant post nasal drip, nausea, extremely itchy chest, and most recently rashes and or raised bumps on my arms, legs, and neck that don‚Äôt itch at all. 

Also, this probiotic has also made my vaginal area smell worse than ever and I don‚Äôt have any infections and have been tested as well. I don‚Äôt know if I have been reacting to a specific strain or certain strains in the probiotic but it‚Äôs been making me feel absolutely miserable. I had to take antihistamines frequently. I was advised from my dietician to stop immediately if possible since it‚Äôs messing with my histamine levels is what she has noticed. Now I need to reset my body and take supplements to help fix this issue on my own. 

However, when I don‚Äôt take the probiotic just to test my theory and none of the symptoms re-appear. I will definitely need to take another probiotic brand going forward. This is the only new food/supplement item that I have added to my regimen this year as well. I‚Äôm really bummed about this because it‚Äôs hard to find a really good and clean probiotic nowadays. However, I rather be safe than sorry especially if it‚Äôs been causing my body issues this whole time unbeknownst to me. 

I wanted to know if am I able to receive refunds for the bottles that I purchased in the past? I am unsure how many I would be eligible to receive a refund for if it‚Äôs all of them or just some of them due to my reactions over the past 5 months. 

If someone could get back to me I would greatly appreciate it. Please feel free to get back to me whenever you can. 

Thank you. 

Best, 
Amber Wordlaw

subject: Prenatal Vitamins
body_text:
Hi! 

My name is Bri and I am in my first trimester using Perelel. 

I chose Perelel because based on my research, I loved that Perelel provided all essential vitamins needed throughout pregnancy and even changed with each trimester, as well as the convenience of daily packs. 

However, the smell of the supplements makes me incredibly nauseous and effects the next few hours of my day. It has lead me to not taking my prenatals at all and I have decided that I will no longer be able to subscribe, unfortunately. 

I would like to return my last shipment and cancel my subscription. Please let me know how to proceed. 

Bri

subject: Missing a vitamin in multiple packs
body_text:
Hi there, I purchased the conception support pack for the 2nd time. The first time I purchased them it was great. However, this pack that I recently purchased had about 4-5 packs that were all missing a vitamin, I believe it was the methyl folate. As that is the beige one, I just noticed it tonight and realized for the past week or so it‚Äôs just been 4 pills and not the 5 it‚Äôs supposed to be. I know that accidents happen, but when you are spending 60+ dollars on supplements to help you conceive it‚Äôs a little frustrating. I have included photos of the supplements and if you‚Äôd like I can send you the serial number for the box. Look forward to hearing back. Thanks, Brittany



Sent from my iPhone

subject: Help with smell/taste!
body_text:
Hello! 

I just started taking your conception support pack after doing extensive research and love your ingredients and mission! I am struggling with the smell/taste but know the benefits outweigh that and do want to continue using Perelel. I was reading some reviews on your website with similar comments from others. I saw you replying to pop the product in the freezer to minimize the smell/taste. I‚Äôm wondering if I can keep the whole pack in the freezer for convenience or if being in there too long will compromise the supplements? 

Any other tips are greatly appreciated! Thank you!!! 

Best, 
Allie Oman
tags: assisted-by-siena, product-sensitivity/smell-taste, general-product/product, complaint/smell-taste, internal/log, email, WCON-P

subject: Refund Request
body_text:
Hello, 
I purchased a 1-month supply of the first trimester prenatal supplements on November 22, 2024. My order number was #739662. I don't know if this is possible, but if it is, can I get a refund for my purchase? I was only able to swallow one pill from the first pack I opened and was unable to take the rest due to the smell of the pills. The smell triggered severe nausea rendering me unable to take any of the other pills in the pack. I still have 29 unopened packs in the box. I cancelled my subscription just a few minutes ago as a result of my inability to continue taking the pills. Please let me know if I can obtain a refund. 
Thank you, Arcelia Sandoval
tags: #739662, internal/log, complaint-date/2024-12-02, cancel/do-not-like, complaint/nausea, complaint/smell-taste, WTR1-P, refund/30-day

subject: Cancel Subscription
body_text:
Good morning, 

I currently have a subscription to the Perelel prenatal vitamins, however my pregnancy has made me extremely nauseous and I am unable to take pills so I need to cancel my subscription. I cannot find a way to cancel my subscription online so I am hoping you can help me cancel, or tell me how I can do so on my own. 

Thanks so much, 

 
Mair√© Gebhard

subject: Conception pack
body_text:
Hi there,

I recently switched from my regular prenatals to your conception pack in the hopes of boosting my fertility. However, within about a week of taking them, I started to have major G.I. upset and had to stop taking them. As soon as I had stopped taking them for two days, I felt much better. I didn‚Äôt mind the strong smell at all. It was more about the way that the supplements seem to have affected my digestive system. I initially got the first pack off of Amazon so I could start them sooner and then I ordered a pack also through your website that I haven‚Äôt opened yet. Is there a way to return them as I know I won‚Äôt be able to continue taking them? The associated order number is 728206.

Thanks,
Blayne Lambert

body_text:

Thank you

Hello, 

I received my vitamins and am unhappy to report that I vomited after taking them. I was taking NatureMade prenatal prior and did not have any issue. While I‚Äôve been on and off nauseous throughout my pregnancy (I am almost 10 weeks), I have not actually thrown up until starting the Perelel vitamins. After such an unpleasant experience, I skipped taking them today. How would you recommend I proceed? I did take the vitamins all at once. Would it help to spread them out throughout the day? 

Thanks 
Christine

body_text:
Hello! 

I hope this email finds you well. I recently purchased your 2nd Trimester pack and started taking them a couple nights ago. 

I had such high hopes for this product but unfortunately I cannot get past the awful smell. I had no nausea or sickness throughout my entire first trimester, but I‚Äôve been gagging and nearly throwing up after taking these pills the last couple of nights. Maybe if it was just one pill per night, I could choke it down, but taking 5 in a row feels like torture. 

Unfortunately this product is not for me, and I will be switching to another brand. Please let me know how to proceed with returning my pack to you for a refund. 

Best, Lexi

subject: Cancelled but says it just got order confirmation?

Katie Ivans

subject: Subscription pause/ return
body_text:
Hello, 

I just received my second box of prenatal (Order #742963) and while I am so happy with the quality and how complete they are, I am simply unable to tolerate them due to 1st trimester nausea. I missed about 7 days of last month and had to buy my old prenatal to hold me over these weeks. I would appreciate any help with pausing my subscription and possibly returning this last order which has not been opened yet. Thank you in advance. 

Ale

subject: Question about a refund
body_text:
Hello, 

My name is Elisa and I just recently bought your third trimester pack. I have been very excited to try out your supplements and have been even recommending them to people all around me after reading up on the products and seeing all the reviews. 

I felt when I first took them on the first day, I could feel a difference in digestion right away and I was even more excited. Yet for the past few days now - I have been feeling randomly sick nauseous, sick, wanting to sleep more, stomach cramping up, and after going to Acupuncture today to feel better - I noticed that after the last few days my symptoms subsided. To wrap it up, after acupuncture, I took my pack for the day with food and water and realized that the symptoms were coming back. 

I am planning on discontinuing use now because I feel the vitamins might be too strong for me and cramping my stomach badly and putting a strain on my body. I had thought maybe it was pregnancy but I have been fine the entire pregnancy until now, not even nauseated like this to the point where I have had to end work early the last few days. 

Is there anyway that I can cancel my membership and and I able to get my money back? 

Sincerely, 

Elisa Parker¬†-- 

Elisa M. Parker, LMHC 

C: 609-332-9420

body_text:
Hello!

Kind of odd, but wanted to let you know that one of my second trimester packs had the wrong medicine in it. I opened another one to confirm and you can see the difference in the two photos below.

Not a huge deal, but also for the price of the product, I hope that the rest of the pills I‚Äôve been taking have been right as there is no indicator other than the box.

Hopefully you guys can work through this. I‚Äôd appreciate a couple dollars (equal to one packet) off my next shipment :)

Thank you!!!!

Michelle Windell

subject: Inquiry
body_text:
Hello,

I‚Äôve recently started taking your Conception Support Pack, and I‚Äôve been experiencing some weird symptoms. I finally figured out this is what‚Äôs been causing them. I‚Äôve been taking the supplements daily with food and water for a little over a week now. I feel completely normal in the morning and the hours leading up to lunch. I then take the supplements with my lunch and then within 30 minutes I begin to experience cramping. The cramping is milder than if I were on my period, however it‚Äôs not easy to ignore. I‚Äôm experience the cramping in my uterus, the lower abdomen muscles, and my back muscles. There are times, not every day, where I get this shock/electricity feeling in my uterus and ovaries that lasts for a few minutes or so. Other than these symptoms, I don‚Äôt really experience any other pain.

I was wondering if this is normal as I adjust to the supplements or if I‚Äôm having an adverse reaction. I don‚Äôt ‚Äòfeel‚Äô allergic to them, but it‚Äôs definitely doing some work on my reproductive system. Any insight would be helpful!

Thank you, Michaela

subject: Vitamins
body_text:
Good morning,
I purchased your conception pack and I‚Äôve been taking it for a few days. The pill pack itself smells so horrible that it makes me want to vomit every time I open it. It smells for lack of a better term, like a nursing home unit, old urine smell. I will not be purchasing this again and don‚Äôt recommend anyone else does. I cannot believe you‚Äôre charging that much money for something that is so horrible smelling. 
I‚Äôm sorry for being so blunt, but it is so bad. My husband can‚Äôt even get near it when I open the pack.
Maybe you could add a good smelling pellet of some kind to help with this.
Sincerely,
Veronica Robison

body_text:
Are these supposed to taste overwhelmingly strong and disgusting? I had trouble with the omega pill but that was nothing compared to the brown pill, I gagged and was barely able to swallow it and it was very, very difficult and uncomfortable
 to not throw it back up. Could not swallow the white pill after the first two and gave up on the rest. Even if these are effective conception ingredients, they are unusable due to the overpowering smell and taste. My husband tried the men's multi support pack
 today and did not have a strong odor or taste with his pills so I am wondering if mine are defective. If they are not defective I would like to return them and cancel my subscription as they are truly horrendous and instantly nauseating unlike anything I have
 ever experienced. I did take with food and a lot of water as instructed. 
 
Paige Strawn

subject: Cancelling Subscription - Requesting refund
body_text:
Good Afternoon, 

I am requesting a refund for my first order as I'm just not enjoying the products. I'm in my 9th week of my third pregnancy and I switched over to you all from Ritual and I continue to feel sick and nauseated when taking the daily vitamins. I've tried taking with food, early in the morning, in the evening, etc and no luck. I end up not feeling well shortly after. 

I did not have this issue with Ritual during my 2nd pregnancy or early in my 3rd prior to switching to Perelel. I'm going to switch back to Ritual and appreciate any refund you can offer. 

Thank you, 
-- 
Devin Bonaventura 
dray8185@gmail.com (mailto:dray8185@gmail.com) 770.617.3413
tags: WTR1-P, #734397, complaint/nausea, complaint-date/2024-12-09, cancel/do-not-like, refund/30-day, internal/log

subject: Feedback + Return Request
body_text:
Hi there,

I‚Äôve been taking Perelel First Trimester ever since I found out I was pregnant and while I love the ingredients and quality, it‚Äôs been extremely difficult to take each day due to the smell and taste. I‚Äôve tried freezing them to help tone it down and tried different food methods but I get nauseous every time I take it and even throw up due to the taste.

I would love to continue with the company but I might need to return so I wanted to inquire about how I might go about that. I bought two boxes and I‚Äôve gone through one but don‚Äôt think I can physically get through the second. If you have any advice, that would be greatly appreciated but wanted to pass along my genuine feedback in hopes maybe some updates happen in the formula down the line! 

Please let me know what I can do, thank you! 
Jordyn Diato

subject: ORDER NO. #754766
body_text:
Good evening, 

I‚Äôm not sure if you can help me but my order was automatically placed on December 2nd and it is now the 10th and per the tracking information it appears my order will be late. 

When I checked the tracking Sunday 12/8, it stated it would be delivered on Monday 12/9. It just needed to arrive at my local¬†post office. I didn‚Äôt get it on Monday. 
When I checked today, it looks like it no longer states when the delivery will be and that it is somehow still in transit ‚Äúto next facility‚Äù. No specific tracking available. 

I am concerned because I am now going on day 3 without my prenatals and I don‚Äôt have a backup. 

Could you resend my order and expedite it if possible? 
Or at the very least refund my money? 
It appears this keeps happening every other month. Deliveries are so slow or delayed and replenished at odd times when I‚Äôve just finished my pack and I have to wait a few days to get my new one. 
I really like this company and I‚Äôd hate to cancel my subscription due to delayed orders. I know it‚Äôs out of the company‚Äôs control however, it‚Äôs still an inconvenience and I‚Äôd rather not stress out and opt for an over the counter prenatal vitamin. 

Thank you in advance.

subject: Cancel subscription
body_text:
Hello! 
I recently (2 weeks ago or so), purchased the subscription to some of your products to get support for my pregnancy. However, your products have worsened my nausea symptoms, and I had to stop taking them. I also burp constantly and it seems like
 I'm having trouble absorbing the vitamins. I canceled my subscription to most products except the probiotics, which the system didn't let me cancel. Please, cancel those as well, as I just met with my Dr. and he was able to prescribe something different for
 me. Thank you 
Additionally, I'd like to¬†return all of the products since I don't think I'll continue using them. Some have already been used, please let me know¬† how to proceed. 
 
Sincerely, 
Teresa Vanek

subject: Product complaint
body_text:
Hello, I recently started taking your conception pack prenatal vitamins which you advertise as being a no-nausea formulation which made me very excited. I have taken them for 3 days now and I have been nauseous every day and gag every time I take them. I had to hold back throwing up yesterday while trying to take them :( not sure if you have any suggestions on how to make it better. I have taken them daily after dinner or lunch with a full glass of water and it just makes it worst. I can taste them in the back of throat all day 

Heather

body_text:
Dear Perellel Customer Service Team, 
I hope this message finds you well. I am writing regarding a recent order of vitamins that I would like to return. Unfortunately, these supplements caused my husband significant stomach discomfort, and despite giving his body ample time to adjust, the issue persisted. 
We have the unopened package from this order, and while I understand your policy allows refunds only for first orders, we were not made aware of this limitation at the time of purchase. It seems unfair to penalize customers in cases where the product is unsuitable, especially when it is unopened and in perfect condition. He really tried to give his body extra time to adjust but it has not worked out for him 
I kindly ask that you make an exception in this case and issue a refund for the unopened vitamins. Thank you for your understanding and consideration. I look forward to hearing from you soon. 

Samantha A. Ozuna

subject: Order 752265
body_text:
Hi there, 
I've been really excited to try Perelel and have appreciated your all's efficient customer service! 
Unfortunately, I don't think perelel is the right prenatal for me. While I was waiting for my vitamin to come in I took a Kroger brand with no symptoms. Once I started taking Perelel I started to feel so jittery and anxious--just couldn't wind
 down even if I was doing my typical routine before bed. I looked into it and I think it might be the high B6 content? I could try it without the anti-nausea med and that may help? I just don't know if this is the right one for me considering the cost and having
 to avoid one of the supplements in the packet. 
Thanks for your help! 
Bree

Good Afternoon! 

I wanted to reach out to see if there was a way to cancel my orders for my prenatal vitamins. Madalyn

subject: Allergy symptoms to vitamin
body_text:
Hi!

I‚Äôve been taking your vitamins throughout my pregnancy and now post partum and it seems I‚Äôve been having mild allergic reactions to the multivitamin. And possibly even the vitamins in the prenatal as well but I have such bad seasonal allergies too it‚Äôs hard to tell. Anyways. I‚Äôm wondering if you‚Äôve ever had anyone say the same and if you have any idea if any of the ingredients are more likely to cause allergy like symptoms for people? Also wondering if you have a detailed ingredient list I could have so I can try to do some research and find a vitamin that may not cause allergies. Thanks!

Julia

subject: Hormone Balance Support
body_text:
Hi there, 

I purchased the hormone balance support pill and it's making me feel pretty sick. I've been taking it with meals but my headaches are persistent and I'm also getting nauseous. I've only been taking 2 per day. 1 in the AM and 1 in the PM. I've previously taken DIM and Berberine with no side effects or symptoms, which is why I am confused. 

If this persists can I ship the product back for a refund? I was really hoping this would work for me, but I might be sensitive to the large amount of Myo-inositol. 

Thank you!

I'm in the first trimester of pregnancy and have been taking the 1st trimester prenatal vitamin pack. I was able to tolerate the conception pack vitamins previously, but the 1st trimester pack is intolerable now to the point where I feel like skipping them as they taste/smell bad and are causing me stomach discomfort with after burps. Is there anything you can suggest? Is there any ingredient in this pack that could be causing my stomach discomfort? Any advice would help. Any other products to take instead? 

Thank you, 
Nikita

subject: Multivitamin
body_text:
Hello!

I am in love with your products, I was previously doing the women‚Äôs multivitamin pack but since I‚Äôm still 18 months postpartum I thought I would give the mom support pack a try.

I have taken it for four days now and have noticed stomach aches and nausea every day. I‚Äôm a little concerned it isn‚Äôt sitting well with me and I have Crohn‚Äôs disease, so I don‚Äôt want to cause too much stomach upset.

subject: Refund of first order
body_text:
