subject: Product Question
body_text:
Product Question
-------------------------------
Do the vitamins from the Conception Support Pack expire after so many days? I am a subscriber and got behind on taking them, so I was going to pause my subscription for a month to take vitamins a few months old. I noticed the multivitamin is a slightly darker gray than the newer vitamins I recently took so want to ask and make sure they are still safe to take. Thank you!

subject: Return?
body_text:
Hello, 
 
I started taking your contraceptive pack recently and really enjoyed taking them. However, they are not agreeing with my system and have been causing severe digestion issues. I just realized the connection and feel much better since I have stopped taking the
 pack. However, I realized too late to stop my next shipment. I have a full unopened contraceptive pack, is this something I can return? 
 
Thank you, 
Emily Dessin

body_text:

subject: Refund
body_text:
Hello, 

I would like to request a refund for my subscription order #751071. 
I believe that these vitamins are very well made and beneficial but the smell and taste is so strong and unpleasant that I can't take them without gagging and I can't bring myself to make my nausea worse every day by taking these. 

Thank you,

subject: Refund Medication
body_text:
Hi there,

I love the work that you all are doing and really wanted to stick with you throughout my pregnancy. I‚Äôve been trying out the 1st trimester pack and I cannot get past the taste of the vitamins. Going into my nausea and vomiting era makes taking them really complicated because of the taste. I would like to get a refund as buying prenatals is not cheap and I don‚Äôt want to just simply throw them away. Please let me know what I can do to get the process started. 

Thank you so much for the work you are doing!

Happy Holidays!

Kayla Washom

subject: Return vitamins
body_text:
Hello,

I started taking your mom postnatal pack vitamins in August after reading about how wonderful they are. I just realized last week that your vitamins have been causing me SEVERE GI distress - constipation, stabbing stomach pain, bloated, general discomfort. When I stopped taking the vitamins, I had zero stomach issues. I was shocked, as I‚Äôd never had vitamins so that to me before. 

I just received a new pack of vitamins that are UNOPENED. Given the above, I will not be taking them. Can I return the product? Please send me a free return shipping label. 

I was a loyal customer for months and would‚Äôve confined to be had your product not been bad for my body. 

Thanks,

Baali 
Sent from my iPhone

subject: Order 704972
body_text:
Hello! 

For months I‚Äôve done my best to try and stomach these prenatals, despite the overwhelming taste of (rancid) fish oil, as they‚Äôre marketed to be the best out there. Recently I learned that many of the prenatals on the market have heavy metals like lead, cadmium (known carcinogen), mercury, and arsenic.  Do your products have any heavy metals in them? 

I‚Äôm pregnant with my first baby and have been using these products since July- I‚Äôm sure you can understand my concern. Thanks in advance. 

Danielle Freeman

 
Sent from my iPhone

subject: 1st trimester pack
body_text:
Hello,

My name is Veronica and I was taking the first trimester prenatal pack for a while. Unfortunately, because of my morning sickness I was unable to swallow the pills and I have a whole pack of unopened and unused first trimester prenatals. I would really like to return them and get my money back since they are a little out of my budget. Is there anyway I can return the prenatals? They are still in the original shipping box and unopened

Thank you 

 Veronica

subject: Concern Regarding Conception Support Pack
body_text:
Dear Perelel Team, 
I hope this email finds you well. 
I recently purchased your conception support pack and have just finished my first pack. While I was initially optimistic about using your product, I am disappointed with the experience‚Äîparticularly with the strong and unpleasant smell of the pills. 
The odor was overwhelming and made it difficult to take the supplements. Unfortunately, this issue has left me feeling unsatisfied with the product. 
I would like to kindly request a refund for my purchase. Please let me know the next steps in the process and if there‚Äôs any additional information you need from me. 
Thank you for your understanding and assistance. I look forward to your response. 
Order Number: 767519 

Best Regards, 
Marissa Petrosino

subject: Request for Refund and Subscription Cancellation
body_text:
Dear Perellel customer service team, 
I hope you're doing well. 
I‚Äôve been taking the vitamins for a few days now, but unfortunately, I‚Äôm not satisfied with the product. The smell makes it difficult to take, and I‚Äôve also experienced a breakout on my back since starting the vitamins. 
As your website mentions a money-back guarantee, I would like to request a refund for my order (Order #770537). 
Additionally, I‚Äôd like to confirm whether I have an active subscription. If so, please cancel it at your earliest convenience. 
Thank you for your assistance. I look forward to hearing from you soon. 
Best regards, 
Annie

subject: 1st trimester prenatal
body_text:
Hi,

My Husband and I have been trying to get pregnant and through research I found it is best to take prenatals before finding out you are pregnant because of the babies development from the start. I came across your brand and decided to go with it for multiple factors, it is women led, research based, and gives back to the community. Although I do not know if I am pregnant yet, I should be able to take a test within the next 12 days, I started the 1st trimester pack today. Although I do not classify myself as someone who has a sensitive stomach, I do have a sensitive gag reflex. I took the prenatal for the first time today and the simplest way I can put it, although I hope I am not comming off as rude I is the smell was really bad. Even post taking it the smell and feelings lingered. I‚Äôm not sure how I will be when I am pregnant but I am scared that I won‚Äôt be able to handle it. Is there any alternatives or anything that can be done to help this. Sorry for the inconvenience. My order was order #780573, the subscription number is MLQY7CGM.

Jenan Jarboun 
jjarboun@yahoo.com
225-505-7765

Jessica

body_text:
Hi! 

I‚Äôm just emailing cause this was a paused subcription cause they made my nausea worse cause I wouldn‚Äôt stand the smell of them at the beginning of my pregnancy. body_text:
Hi, 

I am reaching out about my order. I am in my first trimester and I wanted to write because I was really looking forward to trying the prenatal mixes from Perelel. However after having them for a couple weeks I have to admit I am really disappointed. 

The products are just too sweet. For me to consume all three supplements, is adding three sweet drinks to my day. It‚Äôs very difficult for me to find a time to build in these really sweet beverages. ¬†I was hopeful given the marketing that these products would make me feel healthier but ultimately when I‚Äôm trying to take magnesium before bed I don‚Äôt want to be taking it in a sickeningly sweet form. 

I would like to arrange for a refund if possible, or at least a credit towards unflavored merchandise. 

I‚Äôm so disappointed that these didn‚Äôt work out for me at all! 

Thank you, 

Hailey

This was my first time buying Perelel products last month, and this makes me not want to order them again. Also, your website is extremely not user-friendly. It took me 15 minutes to try to figure out how to cancel my order and it still would not work, which is why I am emailing you. Notify me immediately that you got this message and that you canceled the subscription that I never signed up for and that you have deleted all of my payment information. 

Thank you, Colleen Pedersen.

subject: Order No. #747309
body_text:
Dear Perelel Customer Support, 

I hope this message finds you well. I am reaching out regarding my experience with your prenatal vitamins. Unfortunately, I have not been able to continue taking them as I have consistently felt ill, including vomiting, after each use. The smell and the capsules themselves seem to be a poor fit for me, which is quite disappointing as I was genuinely excited to try your product. 

Given these circumstances, I would like to request a refund for my purchase. Please let me know if you need any additional information from me to process this request. 

Thank you for your understanding and assistance. I look forward to your response. 

Best regards, 
Yamilex Jeffery 
Order No. #747309

subject: Cancel subscription and return last box
body_text:
Hi! I would like to cancel my prescription for the remainder of my pregnancy. These prenatals triggered a lot of sodden nausea for me, even when taken with plenty of food, and I would regularly throw them up right after taking. I have switched to a different brand that is easier on my stomach. If possible I‚Äôd like to return the last box (unopened) that was sent to me, and cancel all orders moving forward. 

Thank you! 
Heather C. Durham Licensed Clinical Mental Health Counselor

Charlotte NC¬†28204 centralpsychcharlotte.com (http://centralpsychcharlotte.com/)

subject: Seal issue x2
body_text:
Hello, 
I previously reached out about a seal that was broken upon arrival of my sleep support. A new product was sent to me very promptly. Unfortunately the same issue has occurred with this bottle. When I opened the box there was product/dust/sleep support inside
 the box and on the outside of the package. When I opened the lid again the seal was broken and the product had leaked. I have provided photos again of the outside of the package where you can see there is product on the outside, as well as inside the lid indicating
 it has leaked prior to me opening it. I have also provided photos of the seal that was open. I‚Äôm not sure the best way to go about this. I think I would like a refund. I live in a very cold climate and feel that maybe the cold does not allow the glue to seal
 the package properly and if another product is shipped the same issue will occur. 
Thank your, 
Shannon Schwartz

body_text:
Hi,

I‚Äôm a new customer and recently ordered/received the Conception pack subscription. I tried it for the first time tonight and took the pills after a big dinner with a large glass of water, as directed. I‚Äôve tried other prenatals from other brands before and had no problem. However, these made me so sick. They gave me horrible stomach pains within the first hour and then terrible upset stomach the rest of the night. Do you have any advice of how else to take these to avoid the side effects? If not, I will need to send them back and cancel my subscription because this is not something I want to go through again every day, as I‚Äôm sure you understand haha.

Thank you,
Brooke

subject: Question
body_text:
Hi there! 

I just started using the conception pack.
 
I am very sensitive to new supplements so I only started with 1 prenatal capsule and plan on adding each different capsule one by one. 

I notice that there is a lingering taste left in my mouth most likely caused by the peppermint leaf powder. I also feel a lump/heaviness in my throat and I am burping a little. 

I am taking 1 prenatal capsule with my dinner. 

Do you have any suggestions how to avoid these uncomfortable things? 

Thank you! 

Stephanie 


Sent from my iPhone

I got these prenatals because they were supposed to help with nausea, they say extended release, but truly are not.
